enish Serum','','publish','closed','closed','','firm-and-replenish-serum','','','2019-12-11 16:30:19','2019-12-11 16:30:19','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=477',0,'product','',0),(579,3,'2019-10-30 13:36:50','2019-10-30 13:36:50','','The Gift of R+R (Replenish + Restore)','','publish','closed','closed','','the-gift-of-rr-replenish-restore','','','2019-12-11 16:25:51','2019-12-11 16:25:51','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=579',0,'product','',0),(481,3,'2019-08-28 13:40:03','2019-08-28 13:40:03','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0943 1 (1)','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0943-1-1','','','2019-08-28 13:40:03','2019-08-28 13:40:03','',477,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0943-1-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(482,3,'2019-08-29 13:39:45','2019-08-29 13:39:45','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Firm + Replenish Serum is our third product made with b-silk™ protein, our proprietary ingredient. Designed to replenish skin before moisturizing, Serum is an essential step in your skincare regimen</strong></em><strong><em>. Here\'s why.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our most concentrated formula yet, <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> is packed with a double dose of b-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our multi-tasking Serum has two main functions. First, Serum works to replenish skin’s barrier after cleansing and exfoliating and prime skin for moisturizer (more on this below). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, b-silk™ protein forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that protects skin from environmental stressors. Over time, b-silk™ protein works to deliver long-term firming, visible lifting, and increased elasticity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What is the skin barrier?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’ve read our Deep Dives on <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/rich-cream-deep-dive/\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> and <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/deep-dive-revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a>, you know that b-silk™ protein works to reinforce the skin barrier, leading to healthy, radiant skin. Here’s a refresher course on the skin barrier. But what exactly is the skin barrier?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also known as the stratum corneum, the skin barrier is the skin’s outermost layer. Its structure is similar to a brick wall, with old skin cells (a.k.a. corneocytes) stacked and held together by lipids and fats.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A healthy skin barrier performs two functions. First, it helps your skin retain moisture by preventing water loss from deeper skin layers. Second, it helps protect your skin from harsh elements like UV rays, pollutants, microbes, and chemicals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your skin barrier\'s function is a direct result of many factors, including nutrition, age, your daily skincare routine, and your surrounding environment. Over time, the barrier starts degrading and gets weaker and a little worse at performing its function. To further complicate matters, every time you cleanse, fats and lipids are stripped from the skin, weakening the skin’s barrier function. This brings on moisture loss, and lets in external aggravators, which further damage the deeper layers of skin by breaking down structural proteins like collagen and elastin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":493} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0943-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-493\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Where does Serum come in?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first job of <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> is to replenish the skin\'s barrier after cleansing and exfoliating. Our Serum is packed with Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF), a cocktail of Amino Acids, PCA, Hyaluronic Acid, and more that the skin naturally creates to keep the stratum corneum and epidermis hydrated. Our Serum delivers a potent dose of NMF so your skin doesn’t need to work so hard to replenish these ingredients on its own.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next up: b-silk™ protein. Our innovative key ingredient mimics your natural barrier function and provides a breathable layer of reinforcement against the elements. B-silk™ protein works to lock in the NMF ingredients so they can do their work on the skin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After applying Serum, you moisturize. Serum is packed with hydrating ingredients, but it feels clean and smooth rather than deeply hydrating. Once skin is primed, apply our lightweight <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> or our decadent <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> to hydrate the skin. By day, top it off with an SPF. By night, you’re good to go.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":491} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_2264.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-491\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What’s Inside?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>B-silk™ protein</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our proprietary ingredient forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that locks moisture in and keeps environmental factors at bay. When b-silk™ protein is applied, tiny silk molecules lock together to form an invisible film on the surface of your skin. Unlike many other barrier-forming ingredients, the b-silk™ protein barrier is not greasy and allows your skin to perform its function while providing vital reinforcement. Read more about <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-b-silk-protein/\">b-silk™ protein here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF)</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF) is a cocktail of Amino Acids, PCA, Hyaluronic Acid, and more that the skin naturally creates to keep the stratum corneum and epidermis hydrated.&nbsp;Here\'s what each of those ingredients does. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Amino Acids</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are two types of Amino Acids: non-essential and essential. Non-essential Amino Acids are produced by the body (such as in NMF). Essential Amino Acids not produced by the body and must be taken in by foods and supplements. Our Serum is made with both types of Amino Acids, including Alanine, Arginine, Aspartic Acid, Glycine, Histidine, Isoleucine, Phenylalanine, Proline, Serine, Threonine, and Valine. Amino Acids work to keep the skin hydrated, strengthen the immune system, and protect skin from free radicals. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Pyrrolidone Carboxylic Acid (PCA)</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pyrrolidone Carboxylic Acid (PCA) is a humectant (a substance used to reduce moisture loss) that is part of the skin\'s NMF.&nbsp;When applied topically, PCA helps replenish the NMF for skin that appears hydrated, smooth, and firm. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Hyaluronic Acid&nbsp;</strong>(HA)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hyaluronic Acid (HA) is another powerful humectant found in the skin’s Natural Moisturizing Factor. And we mean powerful – HA can hold approximately 1,000 times its weight in water. HA works like a magnet to hold moisture, helping your skin look hydrated and healthy. When our skin is more hydrated, it appears plumper and fine lines are less visible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Ceramides&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ceramides are essential lipids that help restore skin integrity and elasticity, fortify the skin barrier, and make the skin look plump and firm. They are naturally produced by the skin, but can be depleted by cleansing, chemicals, and environmental factors. Firm + Replenish Serum contains three types of naturally-occurring ceramides: Ceramide AP, EOP, and NP. All of these have a slightly different molecular structure and work in concert to support barrier function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Let’s See the Results.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a consumer trial, users reported results in as little as seven days. With continued use, skin keeps getting better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Want to see for yourself? Shop <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> today to get started.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":494} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Data_581px-868x768.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-494\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Deep Dive: Firm + Replenish Serum','Firm + Replenish Serum is our third product made with b-silk™ protein, our proprietary ingredient. Designed to replenish skin before moisturizing, Serum is an essential step in your skincare regimen. Here\'s why.','publish','open','open','','deep-dive-firm-replenish-serum','','','2019-09-05 15:13:53','2019-09-05 15:13:53','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=482',0,'post','',0),(78,3,'2019-07-08 19:48:34','2019-07-08 19:48:34','','Stories','','publish','closed','closed','','stories','','','2019-07-22 07:37:39','2019-07-22 07:37:39','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?page_id=78',0,'page','',0),(79,3,'2019-07-08 19:48:34','2019-07-08 19:48:34','','Post List','','inherit','closed','closed','','78-revision-v1','','','2019-07-08 19:48:34','2019-07-08 19:48:34','',78,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/78-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(81,3,'2019-07-18 15:11:46','2019-07-18 15:11:46','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>B-silk™ protein is our first proprietary ingredient, and we think it\'s pretty incredible. But don\'t take our word for it – see for yourself. Here\'s your primer on our not-so-secret ingredient.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein is the key ingredient in our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> and our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a>. It\'s clean, it\'s sustainable, and it really works. To find out how it works, we\'ll need to get a little technical.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein was inspired by the properties of spider silk. Spider silk has a unique molecular makeup makes it stronger and stretchier than the commonly used silkworm silk. Like natural silk proteins, b-silk™ protein is a high molecular weight structural protein that complements the vital functions of your skin and reinforces its extracellular matrix (a.k.a. collagen and elastin, the proteins that begin to break down as we age). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":284} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0932.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-284\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Silk proteins are strong, soft, and biocompatible, making them perfectly suited for use in skincare products. (<a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/silk-101/\">Read more in our Silk 101 here</a>.) Silk proteins are used in other skincare products, but they are usually fragmented into smaller pieces using a process called molecular hydrolysis. This process breaks down a bigger molecule (polymer) into many smaller molecules (monomers) by severing the bonds that hold monomers together. Hydrolyzed silk proteins are highly processed and degraded, which can compromise their valuable properties and effects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein, on the other hand, is not hydrolyzed. Through rigorous testing, we came up with a formula that keeps the molecular structure intact. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":310} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0098.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-310\"/><figcaption><em>Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream (left) and Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer (right)</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein is engineered in our labs using a simple fermentation process in which the inputs are yeast, water, sugar, and salt. The proteins are left intact – never hydrolyzed. The intact molecular structure delivers more benefits, for better results. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why? The size of a protein is often measured in Daltons. B-silk™ protein is ~80,000 Daltons, while hydrolyzed silk can be less than 500 Daltons. That is two orders of magnitude (or 100 times) smaller. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Clinically-tested efficacy lies at the heart of our process. In our first clinical trial, 33 women with a mixture of normal, dry, and combination skin tested products containing b-silk™ protein. Here are the results after four and eight weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":278} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts4-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-278\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":281} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts8-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-281\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s not just good for your skin. B-silk™ protein is clean, sustainable, and 100% cruelty-free. In short, there\'s a lot to love.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We\'d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What is B-silk™ Protein?','B-silk™ protein is our first proprietary ingredient, and we think it\'s pretty incredible. See for yourself. Here\'s your primer on our not-so-secret ingredient.','publish','closed','closed','','what-is-b-silk-protein','','','2019-08-27 08:49:41','2019-08-27 08:49:41','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=81',0,'post','',0),(246,3,'2019-07-20 10:33:45','2019-07-20 10:33:45','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0177','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0177','','','2019-07-20 10:33:45','2019-07-20 10:33:45','',83,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0177.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(247,3,'2019-07-20 10:34:10','2019-07-20 10:34:10','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0081','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0081','','','2019-07-20 10:34:10','2019-07-20 10:34:10','',83,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0081.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(248,3,'2019-07-20 10:34:25','2019-07-20 10:34:25','','18B_MODEL-PRODUCT_MUNIRA_RICH-CREAM_4X5_05','','inherit','open','closed','','18b_model-product_munira_rich-cream_4x5_05','','','2019-07-20 10:34:25','2019-07-20 10:34:25','',83,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/18B_MODEL-PRODUCT_MUNIRA_RICH-CREAM_4X5_05.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(249,3,'2019-07-20 10:36:21','2019-07-20 10:36:21','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0072','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0072','','','2019-07-20 10:36:21','2019-07-20 10:36:21','',83,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0072.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(82,3,'2019-10-12 15:11:40','2019-10-12 15:11:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>To understand why Eighteen B formulations work, you\'ll have to start at the beginning: with silk. Here\'s how we harnessed the power of silk to cre</strong></em><strong><em>ate b-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Imagine a piece of silk fabric. It’s soft, smooth, and lightweight. Like the fabric, silk proteins are soft and silky, but they’re also incredibly strong. The most common silk used in consumer products is silk made by silkworms, but silk made by spiders is even stronger. It\'s stronger than steel and nearly as tough as Kevlar, making it one of the strongest materials found in nature. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On a molecular level, silk is a structural protein made of a long chain of repeating units, like a pearl necklace. This pattern of repeating segments is what makes silk so strong. (FYI, b-silk™ protein has 18 of these “pearls.” That’s where our name comes from.)&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Silk is tough, but it’s also highly biocompatible. When the body doesn’t recognize a material, it can elicit a negative immune response. Silk, on the other hand, is similar enough to your body’s molecular structure that your body doesn’t reject it. This makes silk ideally suited for regenerating and rebuilding human tissues. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Scientists use silk for sutures, surgical scaffolds and injectables, and vaccine stabilization. It has also been used as a scaffolding material to grow tissues ex vivo (think in a decked out petri dish called a bioreactor) such as skin, cornea, bone, blood vessel, liver, kidney, and cardiac tissue. As a bonus, silk is biodegradable and will eventually return to the earth as protein.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/silk-innovations-were-watching/\">Read more about exciting innovations in silk here.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So yes, silk is pretty wonderful. The biggest challenge is gathering a lot of it. Silkworm silk is more abundant than spider silk, but it’s difficult to convert silkworm fibers into a form that can be incorporated into skincare products. That’s where Eighteen B comes in. In our labs, we make b-silk™ protein, a protein inspired by spider silk using a fermentation process that’s sustainable and cruelty free.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient, forms a light, breathable barrier that simultaneously provides all-day hydration. By replenishing your vital barrier function, it leaves your skin incredibly soft and smooth while visibly firming, lifting, and increasing overall radiance. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-b-silk-protein/\">Want to learn more about b-silk™ protein? Dive deeper here.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We\'d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Silk 101: Here\'s Why Silk Makes Better Skincare','To understand why Eighteen B formulations work, you\'ll have to start at the beginning: with silk. Here\'s how we harnessed the power of silk to create b-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient.','publish','closed','closed','','silk-101','','','2019-10-13 09:02:25','2019-10-13 09:02:25','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=82',0,'post','',0),(265,3,'2019-07-20 11:24:01','2019-07-20 11:24:01','','18B_MODEL_BOJANA_4X5_08-2','','inherit','open','closed','','18b_model_bojana_4x5_08-2','','','2019-07-20 11:24:01','2019-07-20 11:24:01','',82,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/18B_MODEL_BOJANA_4X5_08-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(228,3,'2019-07-19 12:23:26','2019-07-19 12:23:26','','18B_MODEL_BOJANA_4X5_08-1','','inherit','open','closed','','18b_model_bojana_4x5_08-1','','','2019-07-19 12:23:26','2019-07-19 12:23:26','',82,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/18B_MODEL_BOJANA_4X5_08-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(273,3,'2019-07-20 12:27:29','2019-07-20 12:27:29','','resized eighteenb-natasha-8435 (1)','','inherit','open','closed','','resized-eighteenb-natasha-8435-1','','','2019-07-20 12:27:29','2019-07-20 12:27:29','',115,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/resized-eighteenb-natasha-8435-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(83,3,'2019-07-20 10:11:36','2019-07-20 10:11:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Our Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream is chock-full of b-silk™ protein</strong></em>, <em><strong>essential lipids, and hydrating oils. These ingredients work together to restore and maintain your skin’s barrier function. How does it work? We thought you\'d never ask. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What is the skin barrier?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream is packed with b-silk™ protein to reinforce the skin barrier. What is the skin barrier? Also known as the stratum corneum, this is the outermost layer of the skin. Its structure is similar to a brick wall, with old skin cells (a.k.a. corneocytes) stacked and held together by lipids and fats. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A healthy skin barrier performs two functions. First, it helps your skin retain moisture by preventing water loss from deeper skin layers. Second, it helps protect your skin from harsh elements like UV rays, pollutants, microbes, and chemicals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":246} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0177.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-246\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your barrier’s function is a direct result of many factors, including nutrition, age, your daily skincare routine, and your surrounding environment. Over time, the barrier starts degrading and gets weaker and a little worse at performing its function. This brings on moisture loss, and lets in external aggravators, which further damage the deeper layers of skin by breaking down structural proteins like collagen and elastin. To further complicate matters, every time you cleanse, fats and lipids are stripped from the skin, weakening the skin\'s barrier function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":248} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/18B_MODEL-PRODUCT_MUNIRA_RICH-CREAM_4X5_05.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-248\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s where Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream comes in. B-silk™ protein, our innovative key ingredient, mimics your natural barrier function and provides a breathable layer of reinforcement against the elements. Natural lipids and fats replenish your skin barrier, anti-inflammatory ingredients calm your skin, while active oils stimulate cell turnover and work to fight signs of aging. Here\'s an introduction to the key players. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What\'s Inside?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>B-silk™ protein </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Call in the reinforcements! Our proprietary ingredient forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that locks moisture in and keeps environmental factors at bay. When b-silk™ protein is applied, tiny silk molecules lock together to form an invisible film on the surface of your skin. Unlike many other barrier-forming ingredients, the b-silk™ protein barrier is not greasy and allows your skin to perform its function while providing vital reinforcement. Read more about <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-b-silk-protein/\">b-silk™ protein here</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Ceramides&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ceramides are essential lipids that help restore skin integrity and elasticity, fortify the skin barrier, and make the skin look plump and firm. They are naturally produced by the skin, but can be depleted by cleansing, chemicals, and environmental factors. The Rich Cream contains three types of naturally-occurring ceramides: Ceramide AP, EOP, and NP. All of these have a slightly different molecular structure and work in concert to support barrier function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Gentianaceae Leaf Extract&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Indian Gentian plant is a medicinal herb native to the Himalayas, and used as a traditional Ayurvedic herb for centuries. It has been shown to help with self-regeneration of the skin and to improve the look of fine lines and wrinkles.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Phytosphingosine&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Phytosphingosine is a naturally occurring lipid found in your skin\'s outer layers. It plays an important role in protecting and nourishing your skin. Phytosphingosine acts as a skin conditioning agent as well as an anti-inflammatory agent, calming and soothing irritated skin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Sunflower Seed Oil&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sunflower seed oil is a powerful source of vitamins, nutrients, and antioxidants. It is naturally rich in Vitamin E, an antioxidant that helps protect the skin from environmental stressors. It also contains omega-6 (linoleic) fatty acid, which helps decrease inflammation and stimulates new cell growth, and beta-carotene, which is beneficial for the healthy appearance of skin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Let\'s See the Results.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ll take any chance to show off our data. B-silk™ protein is clinically shown to deliver results in just four weeks. With continued use, skin keeps getting better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Want to see for yourself? <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Shop Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream today to get started</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":278} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts4-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-278\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":281} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts8-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-281\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We\'d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Deep Dive: Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream','Our Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream is packed with nurturing ingredients that restore and maintain your skin’s barrier function. How does it work? We thought you\'d never ask.','publish','closed','closed','','rich-cream-deep-dive','','','2019-08-16 09:31:26','2019-08-16 09:31:26','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=83',0,'post','',0),(506,3,'2019-09-10 11:48:53','2019-09-10 11:48:53','','eighteenb-wendy-0275','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-wendy-0275','','','2019-09-10 11:48:53','2019-09-10 11:48:53','',505,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/eighteenb-wendy-0275.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(507,3,'2019-09-10 11:56:17','2019-09-10 11:56:17','','20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1815','','inherit','open','closed','','20190727_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1815-2','','','2019-09-10 11:56:17','2019-09-10 11:56:17','',505,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1815-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(509,3,'2019-09-12 18:50:30','2019-09-12 18:50:30','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>At Eighteen B, we believe that protecting the skin barrier is essential to maintaining healthy skin. B-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient, was designed to support the skin\'s natural barrier. Here\'s how b-silk™ protein works and why it matters.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eighteen B harnesses the power of silk – one of the strongest materials in the natural world – to reinforce skin’s natural barrier. Engineered in a patented process by Lindsay Wray, PhD, b-silk™ protein creates a lightweight, breathable barrier that delivers nourishing ingredients to the skin and locks environmental stressors out for skin that looks healthy and radiant.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Why silk?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Imagine a piece of silk. It’s soft, lustrous, and lightweight. Silk proteins are also soft and silky, but they’re incredibly strong – stronger than steel and nearly as tough as Kevlar. Due to this strength and biocompatibility, silk is used in wound healing, sutures, and surgical scaffolds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What is b-silk™ protein?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a decade of research, our Chief Science Officer, Lindsay Wray, PhD, engineered b-silk™ protein to mimic natural silk protein.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When natural silk proteins are used in skincare products, they’re typically hydrolyzed, or cut into small pieces, which compromises their molecular structure. B-silk™ protein molecules remain intact, allowing them to help smaller molecules – like the hydrating components in our formulations – work more efficiently.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein is made through a patented fermentation process using yeast, water, sugar, and salt. That means it’s vegan, cruelty-free, and sustainable.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>How does b-silk™ protein work?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like a silk scarf, b-silk™ protein forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that locks restorative ingredients in and locks environmental stressors out. In short, it helps support your natural skin barrier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><span style=\"\"><a style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\" href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers\">Support your skin barrier. Shop Eighteen B.</a></span></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why is protecting the skin barrier so important? The skin barrier is the outermost layers of the epidermis, also known as the stratum corneum. If you imagine the stratum corneum as a brick wall, the “bricks” are corneocytes – which produce Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF) to stay hydrated – and the “mortar” is naturally produced lipids like Cholesterol and Ceramides. This “brick wall” is the primary barrier between your skin and the world. An unhealthy skin barrier can lead to dryness, dullness, and irritation.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When applied, our b-silk™ protein forms a long-lasting barrier to support your natural barrier function. It acts as a vital defense against environmental stressors as well as a moisture depot, delivering immediate and sustained hydration throughout the day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By replenishing your vital barrier function, b-silk™ protein is clinically shown to improve texture and smoothness for skin that looks firm, youthful, and healthy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Scientifically designed, scientifically tested.&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein is clinically shown to improve skin’s appearance in as little as four weeks. With continued use, results keep getting better.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":278} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts4-Weeks-1-1024x467.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-278\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":281} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts8-Weeks-1-1024x465.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-281\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Why B-silk™ Protein Belongs In Your Skincare Regimen','B-silk™ protein forms a breathable barrier that keeps nourishing ingredients in and locks environmental stressors out. In short, it helps support your natural skin barrier. Here\'s why that matters.','publish','open','open','','why-b-silk-protein-belongs-in-your-skincare-regimen','','','2019-10-16 12:14:06','2019-10-16 12:14:06','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=509',0,'post','',0),(511,3,'2019-09-12 18:46:12','2019-09-12 18:46:12','','20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1399','','inherit','open','closed','','20190727_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1399','','','2019-09-12 18:46:12','2019-09-12 18:46:12','',509,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1399.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(513,3,'2019-09-19 15:37:33','2019-09-19 15:37:33','','Silk Innovations','','inherit','open','closed','','silk-innovations','','','2019-09-19 15:37:33','2019-09-19 15:37:33','',512,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Silk-Innovations.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(517,3,'2019-09-22 10:21:38','2019-09-22 10:21:38','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>We’re all familiar with the signs of aging skin (or we will be soon enough!) The skin becomes thinner, less plump, and less elastic over time. But what exactly is happening below the surface? Here’s a look at the biology of skin aging.&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Intrinsic vs. extrinsic factors of skin aging</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Skin aging is caused by a combination of intrinsic factors and extrinsic factors. Intrinsic factors are inevitable, pre-determined by a person\'s genetics. As explained by Miranda A. Farage, MSc, PhD, in her <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3840548/\">study</a> on aging skin, intrinsic factors also include changing hormones. For example, falling levels of estrogen contribute to thinning skin in women. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The signs of intrinsic aging look different for everyone, but a few are quite common. As we age, our skin starts to <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6047276/\">produce less collagen and elastin</a>. The weakened connection to the epidermis causes skin to wrinkle. Our sweat and oil glands become less active, which causes dry skin. In turn, dry skin makes wrinkles more apparent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While intrinsic aging is inevitable, we have the power when it comes to extrinsic factors. Extrinsic factors of aging, including sun exposure, pollution, and smoking, are shown to make a major difference on the health of our skin. Sun exposure is shown to account for <a href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/j.1468-2494.2007.00415.x#b21\">up to 90%</a> of visible skin aging. Signs of sun exposure are deep wrinkles, thickened skin, dullness, and, at its worst, skin cancer.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What can we do slow the signs of aging?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":520} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1070.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-520\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s not all bad news! While aging is a fact of life, there’s a lot we can do to help slow down the visible signs of extrinsic skin aging. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">1. Shield your skin from the sun.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You’ve heard this time and time again, but we have to reiterate: it\'s so important to limit your exposure to UV rays. This goes beyond wearing sunscreen. Doctors recommend wearing a hat and staying out of the sun during peak hours whenever possible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">2. Exercise regularly.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a <a href=\"https://well.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/04/16/younger-skin-through-exercise/\">study</a> at McMaster University in Ontario, researchers found that those who exercise regularly have healthier skin than those who do not. The results found that of the participants over age 40 who exercise regularly had healthier stratum corneums (AKA skin barriers) and thicker dermis layers than the sedentary group. Their skin was biologically closer to the skin of the 20- and 30-year old participants than the sedentary group of the same age. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">3. Protect your skin barrier.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aging affects the skin barrier in several ways. The skin barrier, or the stratum corneum, is the outermost layer of the epidermis. As described by Dr. Eung Ho Choi in his <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0738081X19300768\">study</a> on aging in the skin barrier, the functions and structures that are disrupted include the permeability function, lipid synthesis and processing, hydration of the stratum corneum, the pH of the stratum corneum, and the antimicrobial barrier.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3583892/\">Studies show</a> that a healthy skin barrier protects against extrinsic factors like pollution, allergens, irritants, and radiation. Protecting the skin barrier should be an essential part of your skincare regimen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When applied, our b-silk™ protein-packed formulations form a long-lasting barrier that supports the natural barrier function. B-silk™ protein acts as a vital defense against environmental stressors as well as a moisture depot, delivering immediate and sustained hydration for skin that looks fresh, healthy, and youthful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Why Does Our Skin Age and What Can We Do?','We’re all familiar with the signs of aging skin (or we will be soon enough!) But what exactly is happening below the surface? Here’s a look at the biology of skin aging.','publish','open','open','','what-causes-our-skin-to-age','','','2019-10-08 07:41:58','2019-10-08 07:41:58','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=517',0,'post','',0),(518,3,'2019-09-22 09:11:15','2019-09-22 09:11:15','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0989','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0989-2','','','2019-09-22 09:11:15','2019-09-22 09:11:15','',517,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0989.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(529,3,'2019-10-02 05:40:07','2019-10-02 05:40:07','','pH-Scale','','inherit','open','closed','','ph-scale','','','2019-10-02 05:40:07','2019-10-02 05:40:07','',526,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/pH-Scale.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(524,3,'2019-09-27 12:47:53','2019-09-27 12:47:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>There’s a hot new trend in the skincare world – only this time it isn’t an exotic botanical. The industry is buzzing about something more fundamental: protecting the natural skin barrier. Here\'s why it matters more than ever. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We launched Eighteen B with two moisturizers designed to support the natural skin barrier. In the early days, however, we often encountered the same hurdle: many consumers had never heard of the skin barrier (or cared about protecting it, for that matter). Now, it seems that the tides are turning. A skincare revolution is underway. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ve recently seen a flood of press surrounding the importance of protecting the skin barrier. We\'re proud to be a part of the conversation and thrilled to see the skin barrier getting the attention it deserves. As we always say, healthy skin requires a healthy skin barrier. Here\'s a look at a few of the recent headlines. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>First things first: what is the skin barrier?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The skin barrier, also known as the stratum corneum, is the outermost layer of the epidermis. We talk about the skin barrier a <em>lot</em> on The Lab, so we’ll let a dermatologist take it from here. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Los Angeles-based dermatologist <a href=\"https://bellaskininstitute.com/\">Anna Guanche</a> told <a href=\"https://www.allure.com/story/what-is-moisture-barrier-skin-care\"><em>Allure</em></a>, “The stratum corneum is a layer of actively shedding dead skin cells. It\'s fortified with a latticework of remaining cell-to-cell connections and the contents of your oil glands that contain lipids.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <em>Allure</em> story continues, “Put simply, the barrier works to keep good stuff in and bad stuff out. Essential water and electrolytes are sealed in, explains Guanche, which keeps skin looking smooth and dewy. At the same time, it protects the skin from dehydration and repels irritants in the air.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Why is the skin barrier at risk?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why is the skin barrier all the rage all of a sudden? As the<em> </em><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/30/style/all-of-those-products-are-making-your-skin-worse.html\"><em>New York Times</em></a> reported in July, “Ask aestheticians and dermatologists what problem they’re seeing these days, and as often as not the answer is a broken-down skin barrier.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ve dug ourselves into this hole. Dr. Whitney Bowe, a New York-based dermatologist, told the <em>New York Times</em>, “It’s largely a product of our own obsession with squeaky clean and using product upon product upon product.” When combined with pollution and environmental aggressors, “you have a recipe for skin barrier disaster,” says the <em>Times</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, spoke to <a href=\"https://www.thezoereport.com/p/eighteen-bs-new-firm-replenish-serum-fills-a-gap-in-your-skincare-routine-you-probably-dont-know-exists-exclusive-18703335\">The Zoe Report</a> on the potential harm of cleansing. Lindsay said, \"In our research, it became clear that one of the most disruptive things we do to our skin’s natural barrier is to cleanse and exfoliate. Cleansing is essential to healthy skin, of course, to remove dirt and make up. In the process, however, cleansers strip the barrier function of some important natural moisturizing factors.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Protect your skin barrier. <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers\">Shop Eighteen B now</a>.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dr. Bowe told the <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/youre-probably-washing-your-face-wrong-11568992522\"><em>Wall Street Journal</em></a>, “when we cleanse, our skin should feel hydrated, smooth and nourished, not tight.” The story continued, “While overwashing can be the culprit, so can washing with products that are too harsh.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>How do you know if your skin barrier is compromised?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your skincare concerns could be related to a compromised skin barrier without you even knowing it. According to the <em>Wall Street Journal</em>, “When that delicate protective barrier is compromised, skin can feel dehydrated, reactive and experience inflammatory conditions like acne.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dr. Kenneth Mark, a New York-based dermatologist, spoke about this for <em>Allure</em>. “Skin might look and feel rough, dull, flaky, inflamed, red, and itchy,” Dr. Mark said. He does mention, however, that these symptoms can also be caused by dehydration, sun, wind, or other factors.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What can we do to support the skin barrier?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thankfully, this is a problem we can control. As a recent story for <a href=\"https://www.shefinds.com/collections/best-serum-for-wrinkles-and-firming/\"><em>SheFinds</em></a> reports, “dermatologists stress the importance of following a nourishing and reparative skincare routine with products that strengthen the skin barrier.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SheFinds continued, “One serum that should be on everyone’s radar is Eighteen B’s new <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">B-silk™ Protein Firm + Replenish Serum</a>, a formula that replenishes skin by forming a protective barrier that helps lock in moisture and other restorative ingredients using the brand’s innovative b-silk™ protein.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s true – our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> was specifically designed to support the skin barrier. Our multi-tasking Serum has two main functions. First, Serum works to replenish skin’s barrier after cleansing and exfoliating and prime skin for moisturizer. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, b-silk™ protein, our proprietary key ingredient, forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that supports the skin barrier and protects skin from environmental stressors. Over time, b-silk™ protein works to deliver long-term firming, visible lifting, and increased elasticity.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s safe to say the skin barrier revolution is underway. Environmental aggressors better watch out. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','People are Buzzing About the Skin Barrier Revolution','There’s a new trend in the skincare world, and it\'s not an exotic botanical. The industry is buzzing about protecting the natural skin barrier. Here\'s why it matters more than ever. ','publish','closed','closed','','the-press-is-buzzing-about-the-skin-barrier','','','2019-10-02 05:52:00','2019-10-02 05:52:00','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=524',0,'post','',0),(520,3,'2019-09-22 10:23:59','2019-09-22 10:23:59','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1070','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1070-2','','','2019-09-22 10:23:59','2019-09-22 10:23:59','',517,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1070.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(525,3,'2019-09-27 13:17:45','2019-09-27 13:17:45','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1250','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1250','','','2019-09-27 13:17:45','2019-09-27 13:17:45','',524,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1250.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(526,3,'2019-10-02 05:48:24','2019-10-02 05:48:24','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>We love talking about the skin barrier, and this week we\'re diving deeper. We’re taking a closer look at the acid mantle, the outermost layer of the skin barrier. Here\'s an introduction to the acid mantle, how it affects the pH of your skin, and why it matters.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’re a faithful reader of The Lab, you’re well versed on the finer points of the skin barrier, AKA the stratum corneum. (If you’re new here, there\'s still time to catch up. Read some recent coverage on the skin barrier <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/the-press-is-buzzing-about-the-skin-barrier/\">here</a>.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you imagine the skin barrier as a brick wall with bricks made of corneocytes and mortar made of lipids, consider the acid mantle as a fresh coat of paint. The acid mantle is a thin film made of natural oils, sebum, and sweat that sits on top of the skin. If you feel a sudden urge to wash your face, don\'t act so fast. The acid mantle does important work: it prevents infections, seals in moisture, and helps skin maintain its pH.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before we go deeper, let’s take a step back and talk about pH. As you learned in chemistry class, pH stands for “potential of Hydrogen.” PH measures the acidity and alkalinity of a solution. A pH of 7 is neutral, like water. A pH higher than 7 means a solution is alkaline. A pH lower than 7 means the solution is acidic.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":529} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/pH-Scale-1024x603.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-529\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our skin is slightly acidic, with a pH in the <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18489300\">range of 4 - 6</a>. But its pH is delicate. It’s easy to neutralize the acid mantle and alter the pH of your skin by using skincare products that are too alkaline.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why should we worry about damaging the acid mantle? A compromised acid mantle can cause skin barrier problems like inflammation, irritation, and, according to <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5605222/\">some researchers</a>, acne.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At Eighteen B, our formulations were designed to support the skin barrier. That means all our products have a pH in a safe, slightly acidic range. The pH of our Firm + Replenish Serum, Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream, and Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer all fall within a range of 5 - 7.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As skin barrier protection garners more attention in the skincare world, the pH of products is gaining more attention. In South Korea, it\'s common for skincare brands to list the pH of their products on the label. In the United States, this is not yet the norm. If you’d like to know the pH of the products you’re using, buy a pack of litmus tests online and test them yourself. Just think how proud your chemistry teacher would be. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Why the pH of Your Skin Matters','This week, we’re taking a closer look at the acid mantle, the outermost layer of the natural skin barrier. Here\'s how the acid mantle affects skin\'s pH and why it\'s so important.','publish','open','open','','why-the-ph-of-your-skin-matters','','','2019-10-02 09:47:22','2019-10-02 09:47:22','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=526',0,'post','',0),(527,3,'2019-10-01 19:57:43','2019-10-01 19:57:43','','2N2A8701','','inherit','open','closed','','2n2a8701','','','2019-10-01 19:57:43','2019-10-01 19:57:43','',526,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/2N2A8701.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(528,3,'2019-10-01 19:59:10','2019-10-01 19:59:10','','2N2A8701','','inherit','open','closed','','2n2a8701-2','','','2019-10-01 19:59:10','2019-10-01 19:59:10','',526,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/2N2A8701-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(530,3,'2019-10-04 10:58:33','2019-10-04 10:58:33','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Our b-silk™ protein is made through a patented fermentation process where the inputs are yeast, water, sugar, and salt. While the specifics of our process are under lock and key, there’s a lot we can say about how we make b-silk™ protein. Call us nerdy, but we think it’s pretty cool.</em></strong><em> </em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What is Fermentation?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here’s a quick introduction to the science of fermentation. Fermentation is a metabolic process where microorganisms break down molecules like glucose into another substance. This process is used to make beer, kombucha, kimchi, cheese, and lots of good things we eat. However, scientists use fermentation for much more than boozy drinks and sour foods. Industrial fermentation is used to make medicines, vaccines, insulin, and other substances that are useful to humans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>History of Fermentation&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fermentation dates back many millenia. Scientists have found <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0305440316000170\">evidence</a> that Scandinavian people were fermenting fish at least 9,200 years ago. As for boozy drinks, evidence of the earliest known alcoholic beverage was found in Henan Province, China. The ancient cocktail, made from rice, honey, and fruit, dates back approximately 9,000 years. Fermentation had particularly useful applications during these times, as fermented food keeps much longer than fresh food. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The term “fermentation” was coined in the 19th century by French chemist Louis Pasteur. Pasteur used the word to describe the process in which microorganisms like yeasts are grown without air, or anaerobically. Pasteur also learned that ethyl alcohol and carbon dioxide aren’t the only substances created by fermentation, which paved the way for industrial fermentation.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>How we make B-silk™ Protein</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At Eighteen B, we carry out our fermentation in our very own labs. While our process works seamlessly today, the exact recipe took many years to devise. Our engineers were able to teach yeast cells how to produce our proprietary b-silk™ protein when undergoing fermentation. This is the same process that scientists use to create insulin and other life-saving drugs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We begin with a small bottle of solution made with yeast, water, sugar, and salt. To jump start the fermentation process, we shake it up to produce bubbles of oxygen, which the yeast uses as fuel to convert the sugar. We then move this solution into larger vats with more sugar, nutrients, and water. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From there, it’s our job to create the right environmental conditions (i.e. the right food, oxygen, temperature, pH, etc) to make the cells happy so they continue to grow and produce our protein at a high quality. It’s essential to keep the environment as sterile as possible, as any contaminants can ruin the batch. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’ve determined the right conditions through a combination of scientific and engineering principles and trial and error. Some elements are very well-studied, such as the ideal temperature range to grow different types of yeast, while others required more experimentation. After settling on the right conditions, we’re able to replicate the same outcome every time. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a few days, we’re left with what we call the “fermentation broth,” which includes water, trace amounts of leftover nutrients and other fermentation byproducts, and a lot of b-silk™ protein. We put the solution through a patented purification process that includes several steps of removing different ingredients from the broth. Finally, we dry the protein carefully so the proteins remain intact. The end result is our b-silk™ protein in powder form. From there, it goes into our formulations to make your skin better. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The Magic of Fermentation: How We Make B-silk™ Protein','Our b-silk™ protein is made through a patented fermentation process. The specifics are under lock and key, but here\'s a peek at how we make b-silk™ protein. Call us nerdy, but we think it’s pretty cool. ','publish','open','open','','the-magic-of-fermentation-how-we-make-b-silk-protein','','','2019-10-04 18:45:21','2019-10-04 18:45:21','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=530',0,'post','',0),(531,3,'2019-10-04 10:50:56','2019-10-04 10:50:56','','2N2A8463','','inherit','open','closed','','2n2a8463','','','2019-10-04 10:50:56','2019-10-04 10:50:56','',530,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/2N2A8463.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(532,3,'2019-10-04 11:02:39','2019-10-04 11:02:39','','2N2A8463','','inherit','open','closed','','2n2a8463-2','','','2019-10-04 11:02:39','2019-10-04 11:02:39','',530,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/2N2A8463-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(540,3,'2019-10-17 12:00:39','2019-10-17 12:00:39','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Katie Jane Hughes, editorial and celebrity makeup artist, recently brought Eighteen B to New York Fashion Week, using <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> to prep the models for her signature glow. We talked to Katie, our newest Eighteen B Woman, about skincare, beauty, and staying authentic in a world of over-editing. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instagram is not known for its likeness to reality. Our feeds are filled with carefully curated photos, filtered to a state of perfection that feels far our of reach in real life. Thankfully, our eye gets a break every once in a while courtesy of editorial and celebrity makeup artist Katie Jane Hughes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To be clear, her photos are <em>pretty</em> perfect. Her <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/katiejanehughes/\">Instagram feed</a> features close-up shots of makeup looks on herself and her celebrity clients like Ashley Graham and Kate Bosworth. Scroll through and you\'ll find expertly winged eyeliner, glossy lids, pops of color, full brows, and her signature glowy skin. Katie\'s looks are always gorgeous, but they\'re refreshingly human. Rather than airbrushed into oblivion, skin looks like skin. And to top it off, it all looks like a lot of fun.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":543} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image10.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-543\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many of Katie\'s followers – the Eighteen B team included – came to know and love her through her Instagram Stories. Katie takes us behind the scenes as she gets ready each morning, showing how she crafts her looks from the very beginning. And, as far as Katie is concerned, the beginning means starting with the skin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The skin prep is absolutely the most important part for me. It ends up making everything look so much better when the skin looks real and fresh and light. I think it\'s also the most therapeutic part,” she told us. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Katie sits before two towering shelves of makeup – or at a dressing table when she\'s on the road – and chats, teaches, and sometimes sings while she does her makeup. She is generous with her techniques, showing us the right way to use brushes, where to apply moisturizer, and how to use powder to keep the glow in all the right places. Her videos feel authentic because they are. \"I’m doing it anyway, so why don’t I share it?\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She saves her best stories to her Instagram Highlights so followers can go back and recreate the looks. \"Instagram Highlights is my version of YouTube.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":545} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image4.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-545\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the makeup always feels fresh and exciting, some parts of the process are essential. “The first, most important step is to gently exfoliate, because that moisturizer isn\'t even going to sink in if there’s dead skin on the face. If you start putting moisturizer on and it starts to roll, then that foundation is going to go on horribly.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before moisturizer comes serum. Katie used our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> on the models at the <a href=\"https://www.susanalexandra.com/\">Susan Alexandra</a> show at New York Fashion Week. Susan Alexandra\'s bat mitzvah-themed show featured comedians, writers, and Instagram celebrities as models, some with her candy-colored bags beaded bags pinned to their wigs. The show was fun, fresh, and bursting with color, which means it was perfect for Katie Jane Hughes. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I love serum that has a tightening effect on the skin. If it’s an oil I want it to be glowy, and if it’s not an oil I want it to tighten everything up. That’s what <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> did for us on show day. It made everyone’s skin look great.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":544} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image2.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-544\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The next step is to moisturize. “The thing I consider first about skincare is the texture. I\'m like, \'is this dewy or whipped enough to have the consistency I need it to have?’”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“With <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>, I think that kind of product should go in specific areas first. The high points of the face, or the areas where you want all that glow and radiance – that’s where you should concentrate the product. Then with the little bit of sheen that’s left on your fingers, that should go in the places where you’re feeling tight and dry.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the skin is prepped, she begins building the makeup. When asked for her makeup philosophy, she asked if she could give us a statement instead. “If you feel attracted to something, then you should try it. If you don\'t end up liking it then you can wash it off. It’s makeup! It’s beauty! It’s not that serious.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":546} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image6.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-546\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I\'m a big believer that people should embrace what they’ve got and enhance it with makeup instead of trying to change it with makeup. I think that\'s key.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But Katie is noticing a trend in the opposite direction. \"There’s a movement of over-editing photographs for Instagram. \'What would I look like if my nose was smaller? What if my lips were fuller or my eyes were a bit more upturned?\'\" It’s fun, Katie admits, but “people get immune to this editing style. Then they edit more and more and they just start to become inhuman.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I feel like it\'s creating more insecurities that we don\'t need. And we can do all of that with makeup. You can trick these shapes with makeup.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Katie is quick to say there\'s nothing wrong with caking on the makeup, she hopes to see the trend move towards fresher skin. “What I really want to see happening is makeup looks with bare, bare skin – just concealer around the nose and the mouth. That\'s why I love: Letting the freckles peek through, letting the skin texture be visible, and letting it shine.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not sure where to begin for fresh-faced skin? We recommend starting with a <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">serum</a>, a <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">moisturizer</a>, and Katie Jane Hughes\' Instagram Stories. As she told us, \"there\'s probably a Highlight for that.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Eighteen B Woman: Katie Jane Hughes','We talked to Katie Jane Hughes, editorial and celebrity makeup artist and our newest Eighteen B Woman, about skincare, beauty, and staying authentic in a world of over-editing. ','publish','open','open','','eighteen-b-woman-katie-jane-hughes','','','2019-10-17 15:57:24','2019-10-17 15:57:24','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=540',0,'post','',0),(536,3,'2019-10-08 07:57:58','2019-10-08 07:57:58','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>At Eighteen B, we want to be confident about every ingredient that goes into our formulations. That\'s why we decided not to use silicones in our products. Lindsay, our Chief Science Officer, tells us why she stands by this decision.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we launched Eighteen B, we made the decision not to include silicone polymers in our formulations. The choice was a challenging one. Silicones impart a lovely texture to skincare formulations. They play nicely with makeup and have been shown to act as skin protectants. They have a slippery glide that makes them feel hydrating and easy to apply.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And yet, after extensive research, we came to the conclusion that there is not enough data on the safety and environmental impact of silicones to feel comfortable using them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using silicones in personal care applications is a complex issue. It’s so complex, in fact, that all of the nuances won’t be captured here. Silicone is an amazing material that plays a critical role in many aspects of our lives. Silicones are polymers derived from sand and methyl chloride. These polymers are processed further to create flexible and elastomeric materials. Thanks to their rubbery texture and heat resistance, silicones are frequently used in consumer products like electronics, kitchen supplies, medical devices, automobiles, and, yes, hair- and skincare products.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At Eighteen B, we believe that certain use cases of silicone make a lot of sense, particularly when the product can be reused time and time again. Skincare formulations, on the other hand, are wiped off or rinsed off down the drain and it\'s not clear what happens next. As my mother is a scientist who spent years working to clean up contaminated groundwater in California, this is particularly concerning to me.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for their impacts on human health, silicone polymers are considered to be low-risk, but there are some interesting nuances to this. Cyclic silicones (these are small molecule silicone, not silicone polymers) have recently come under scrutiny. Some data indicates that these chemicals – referred to as D4, D5, and D6 – may have reproductive, developmental toxicity, and/or endocrine disruption concerns. While silicone polymers and cyclic silicones are different molecules, in certain instances the cyclics can be found in trace amounts in silicone polymers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is A LOT of debate about this. The silicones D4, D5, and D6 have been listed as Substances of Very High Concern in the European Union. As we speak, the EU is deciding whether to place additional restrictions on the use of cyclic silicones in personal care products. It’s a hot button topic that will unfold over the next couple of years. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meanwhile, we are continuing to take matters into our own hands. We are working with a group of toxicologist experts to better understand the impact of silicones and other polymers on the environment. Our hope is that, through this research, we can update our definition of “clean beauty” to include a fair and balanced depiction of silicones. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Until then, you can be sure you’ll never see any silicones in Eighteen B products. We\'ve been able to recreate the slick, hydrating texture in our products without using silicones. The texture is so nice, in fact, that we think you\'ll never miss them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ask Lindsay: Why We Decided Not to Use Silicones in Our Products','We want to be confident about every ingredient that goes into our formulations. That\'s why we decided not to use silicones in our products. Lindsay, our Chief Science Officer, tells us why she stands by this decision.','publish','open','open','','ask-lindsay-why-we-decided-not-to-use-silicones-in-our-products','','','2019-10-08 08:13:49','2019-10-08 08:13:49','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=536',0,'post','',0),(537,3,'2019-10-08 07:44:49','2019-10-08 07:44:49','','18B_MODEL + PRODUCT_MUNIRA_RICH CREAM_4X5_05','','inherit','open','closed','','18b_model-product_munira_rich-cream_4x5_05-2','','','2019-10-08 07:44:49','2019-10-08 07:44:49','',536,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/18B_MODEL-PRODUCT_MUNIRA_RICH-CREAM_4X5_05.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(541,3,'2019-10-16 09:45:58','2019-10-16 09:45:58','','image11','','inherit','open','closed','','image11','','','2019-10-16 09:45:58','2019-10-16 09:45:58','',540,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image11.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(543,3,'2019-10-16 09:51:15','2019-10-16 09:51:15','','image10','','inherit','open','closed','','image10','','','2019-10-16 09:51:15','2019-10-16 09:51:15','',540,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image10.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(544,3,'2019-10-16 09:51:49','2019-10-16 09:51:49','','image2','','inherit','open','closed','','image2','','','2019-10-16 09:51:49','2019-10-16 09:51:49','',540,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image2.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(545,3,'2019-10-16 09:52:23','2019-10-16 09:52:23','','image4','','inherit','open','closed','','image4','','','2019-10-16 09:52:23','2019-10-16 09:52:23','',540,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image4.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(546,3,'2019-10-16 09:52:56','2019-10-16 09:52:56','','image6','','inherit','open','closed','','image6','','','2019-10-16 09:52:56','2019-10-16 09:52:56','',540,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/image6.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(547,3,'2019-10-16 12:52:33','2019-10-16 12:52:33','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>At Eighteen B, we believe that healthy skin requires a healthy skin barrier. Dermatologist <a href=\"https://dellmed.utexas.edu/directory/s-tyler-hollmig\">Dr. S. Tyler Hollmig</a> agrees. We reached out to Dr. Hollmig, the Director of Dermatologic Surgery and Director of Laser and Cosmetic Dermatology at the Dell Medical School at the University of Texas at Austin, to ask a few questions about the skin barrier and why it matters</strong></em><strong><em>. Here\'s what he had to say.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>The skin barrier can be complicated. How do you describe the skin barrier to a patient?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The skin barrier is incredibly important and enormously complicated.&nbsp;It helps to keep the bad stuff out and the good stuff in, and also helps us regulate temperature, feel and interact with our surroundings, and even plays an important role in our immune system. You can conceptualize the outer layer of our skin almost like the wall of a castle, with skin cells representing the stones and lipids and other natural elements between the cells as the mortar holding it all together. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is also something called the \"acid mantle,\" where, to take the example even further, a natural acidic film serves almost like a moat surrounding the castle, keeping out bacteria and other potential skin contaminants.&nbsp; So we have a really elegant \"mechanical barrier\" that blocks harsh environmental factors&nbsp;from penetrating our skin, and also helps maintain our inner water balance, but there are so many more amazing things that our skin barrier does for us, as mentioned above! It is clear that a healthy skin barrier is key to our well-being – and also helps us look our best!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What causes the skin barrier to become compromised?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are numerous causes of a compromised skin barrier, and this keeps dermatologists incredibly busy! Genetic factors as well as environmental stressors may all violate the skin barrier. One common cause of poor barrier function is simple: dry skin! When the skin becomes dry, due to weather changes, hereditary causes, or overuse of harsh exfoliating or other agents, the outer layer of the skin loses its ability to protect deeper layers from the environment, leading to skin irritation, dermatitis, and other problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>How can we tell if your skin barrier is weakened?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Typical signs of a poor skin barrier include dry, scaly skin, and red, irritated skin. Itch can derive from poor skin barrier function and be more than a little annoying! Similarly, atopic dermatitis (eczema), and a host of other skin maladies are largely driven by a weakened skin barrier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Do you believe these skin conditions are becoming more common?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More and more patients seems to experience \"sensitive skin.\" This term is thrown around so incredibly commonly – and this is a real problem – but it is difficult to pin down exactly what \"sensitive skin\" means. It manifests in so many different ways, from sensitivity to topical products to eczema to acne. I do believe that environmental changes (increased UV exposure, increased pollution, others) plus overuse of certain harsh cosmetic products or inappropriate combinations of skin products are all playing a role in the increase in sensitive and irritated skin we are seeing in our clinics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What can we do to protect our skin barrier?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>General advice here is to protect the skin from the sun every day – UV protection is key, even when we are not going to be outside as certain harmful wavelengths of light penetrate window glass.&nbsp;Additionally, gentle cleansing to remove makeup and pollutants before bed (avoid harsh scrubs!) is helpful, along with using a moisturizer tailored to the individual patient\'s skin type and environment. In general, fewer products are better than lots of different products and fewer ingredients trump a laundry list of fragrances and preservatives.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have a question for our skincare experts? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Dermatologist Dr. Tyler Hollmig on Why the Skin Barrier is Key','We believe that healthy skin requires a healthy skin barrier. Dermatologist Dr. S. Tyler Hollmig believes it, too. We reached out to ask a few questions about the skin barrier and why it matters.','publish','open','open','','dermatologist-dr-tyler-hollmig-on-why-the-skin-barrier-is-key','','','2019-10-21 12:07:31','2019-10-21 12:07:31','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=547',0,'post','',0),(548,3,'2019-10-16 12:12:04','2019-10-16 12:12:04','','DataChart_523px','','inherit','open','closed','','datachart_523px','','','2019-10-16 12:12:04','2019-10-16 12:12:04','',509,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/DataChart_523px.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(550,3,'2019-10-16 12:41:57','2019-10-16 12:41:57','','20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1506','','inherit','open','closed','','20190727_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1506','','','2019-10-16 12:41:57','2019-10-16 12:41:57','',547,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1506.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(552,3,'2020-01-20 14:40:18','2020-01-20 14:40:18','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>The Eighteen B collection includes our brand new <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/defend-nourish-eye-cream\">Defend + Nourish Eye Cream</a>, <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a>, our award-winning <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a>, and our bestselling <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>. Here\'s how these products work together to support the skin barrier for skin that looks healthy, hydrated, and radiant.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dermatologists agree that a healthy skin barrier is essential for healthy skin. <a href=\"https://dellmed.utexas.edu/directory/s-tyler-hollmig\">Dr. S. Tyler Hollmig</a>, the Director of Dermatologic Surgery and Director of Laser and Cosmetic Dermatology at the Dell Medical School at the University of Texas at Austin, says \"a healthy skin barrier is key to our well-being – and also helps us look our best!\"&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Despite our best efforts, however, we often damage our skin barrier through our skincare regimen. As Dr. Whitney Bowe, a New York-based dermatologist, told the <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/30/style/all-of-those-products-are-making-your-skin-worse.html\"><em>New York Times</em></a>, “It’s largely a product of our own obsession with squeaky clean and using product upon product upon product.” When combined with pollution and environmental aggressors, “you have a recipe for skin barrier disaster,” says the <em>Times</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Eighteen B regimen was designed to support the skin barrier through a multi-faceted approach. </strong>First, our proprietary polypeptide, b-silk™ protein, replenishes the natural barrier. Second, it delivers a boost of hydration and carries potent ingredients to the skin. Finally, it creates a lightweight, breathable barrier that locks nourishing ingredients in and keep environmental stressors out.&nbsp;Here\'s how to build your regimen with Eighteen B. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers\">Start building your regimen with Eighteen B now.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Why is the skin barrier so important? </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Dr. Hollmig explains it, the skin barrier “helps to keep the bad stuff out and the good stuff in, and also helps us regulate temperature, feel and interact with our surroundings, and even plays an important role in our immune system.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the skin barrier is damaged, skin can look dry, scaly, red, and irritated. What’s more, Dr. Hollmig explains, “atopic dermatitis (eczema), and a host of other skin maladies are largely driven by a weakened skin barrier.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What can we do to avoid these conditions? Dr. Hollmig recommends “fewer products are better than lots of different products and fewer ingredients trump a laundry list of fragrances and preservatives.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">How to build your regimen with Eighteen B</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our fragrance-free formulations were designed to support the skin barrier through an easy two- or three-step regimen. Our B-silk™ Protein, a key ingredient in all our formulations, is clinically shown to improve texture and smoothness for skin that looks firm, youthful, and healthy. Here’s how to build your regimen with Eighteen B.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Step one: Replenish the skin barrier with our Firm + Replenish Serum.&nbsp;</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our multi-tasking <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> has two main functions. First, Serum works to replenish skin’s barrier after cleansing and exfoliating. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How? Serum is packed with Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF), a cocktail of ingredients that the skin naturally creates to keep itself hydrated. While the skin produces NMF on its own, these ingredients are easily stripped away by common cleansers, skincare products, and environmental factors.&nbsp;Serum replenishes the skin\'s NMF so the skin doesn\'t need to work as hard. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":507} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1815-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-507\"/><figcaption><em>Firm + Replenish Serum</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, B-silk™ Protein forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that protects the skin from environmental stressors. Over time, B-silk™ Protein works to deliver long-term firming, visible lifting, and increased elasticity.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/deep-dive-firm-replenish-serum/\">Read more about our Firm + Replenish Serum</a></em></strong><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/deep-dive-firm-replenish-serum/\"><strong><em>.</em></strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Step two: Protect the delicate skin around the eye with our Defend + Nourish Eye Cream.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The thin skin around the eyes needs some extra love. Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/defend-nourish-eye-cream\">Defend + Nourish Eye Cream</a> is packed with B-silk™ Protein, which delivers powerful ingredients to this delicate skin while skillfully defending your natural skin barrier. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ Protein forms a lightweight, protective barrier that keeps active ingredients close to the skin so they can do their work. The result? Smoother, more rested looking eyes with less visible wrinkles and faded dark circles. In other words, it’s the eye cream that breaks barriers by building yours. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/why-you-need-eye-cream/\">Read more about why you need an eye cream here.</a></em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ Protein carries some seriously potent active ingredients to the skin. Hydration comes courtesy of powerful emollients and humectants like Squalane, Jojoba Oil, and Hyaluronic Acid. Jasmine Flower Extract helps improve circulation to banish the appearance of dark circles. Finally, Watermelon Rind Extract, Lentil Fruit Extract, and Apple Extract hydrate and replenish skin to reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and crepiness. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you apply, be sure to use your ring finger so you don\'t stretch the skin. Any bit helps! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":685} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/EighteenB_11-21-19_037_web.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-685\"/><figcaption><em>Defend + Nourish Eye Cream</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Step three: Hydrate the skin with our B-silk™ Protein-packed moisturizers.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, you follow up with a moisturizer. (There\'s no need to apply moisturizer on top of Defend + Nourish Eye Cream, but it\'s totally fine if there\'s a little overlap!)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But which to pick? Our collection includes two moisturizers: <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a>, our lightweight gel, and <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>, our deeply nourishing cream.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the textures and some of the active ingredients are unique, both contain moisture-magnet Hyaluronic Acid (HA), three types of naturally-occurring ceramides, and b-silk™ protein. These ingredients work together to hydrate the skin and support skin barrier function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":560} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1146.jpg\" alt=\"Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream (top) and Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer (bottom)\" class=\"wp-image-560\"/><figcaption><em>Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream (top) and Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer (bottom)</em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How you use our moisturizers is entirely up to you. Many of us at Eighteen B use <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> in the morning, as it layers well under SPF and makeup, and <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> at night, which deeply hydrates while we sleep.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That’s not the only way. Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream is a great choice for keeping skin hydrated during the cooler months. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A few of our Eighteen B Women love the feeling of Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream during the day no matter the season. <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-woman-felicia-walker/\">Felicia Walker</a>, the beauty and skincare expert behind the award-winning beauty blog <a href=\"http://thisthatbeauty.com/about/\">ThisThatBeauty</a>, told us, “the Rich Cream works really beautifully under makeup. It doesn’t separate the makeup, it doesn’t make the makeup too greasy.” She also uses Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream as a hack midday. \"I just press it over my skin to give it more bounce and glow, or to refresh makeup if it’s looking a little matte.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-woman-katie-jane-hughes/\">Katie Jane Hughes</a>, editorial and celebrity makeup artist, reaches for our Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream during the day for glowing skin. Her trick? “I think that kind of product should go in specific areas first. The high points of the face, or the areas where you want all that glow and radiance – that’s where you should concentrate the product. Then with the little bit of sheen that’s left on your fingers, that should go in the places where you’re feeling tight and dry.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','This Simple Regimen is Clinically Shown to Deliver Radiant Skin','The full Eighteen B collection includes an eye cream, a serum, and two moisturizers. Here\'s how to build a regimen that supports the skin barrier for skin that looks healthy, hydrated, and radiant.','publish','open','open','','this-simple-regimen-is-clinically-shown-to-deliver-radiant-skin','','','2020-01-21 13:01:58','2020-01-21 13:01:58','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=552',0,'post','',0),(553,3,'2019-10-24 12:07:47','2019-10-24 12:07:47','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0085','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0085-3','','','2019-10-24 12:07:47','2019-10-24 12:07:47','',552,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0085.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(554,3,'201