21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(426,3,'2019-08-11 14:32:05','2019-08-11 14:32:05','','eighteenb-camille-3638 (1)','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3638-1','','','2019-08-11 14:32:05','2019-08-11 14:32:05','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3638-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(427,3,'2019-08-11 14:37:35','2019-08-11 14:37:35','','eighteenb-camille-3597','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3597-2','','','2019-08-11 14:37:35','2019-08-11 14:37:35','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3597-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(428,3,'2019-08-11 08:11:22','2019-08-11 08:11:22','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Our Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer is a refreshing gel that delivers hydrating ingredients and a punch of b-silk™ protein. These ingredients work together to hydrate and reinforce skin’s barrier function. Want to learn how it works? Great – we can talk about Hydrogel all day.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> is our lightweight gel moisturizer. It’s breezy, it’s breathable, and it layers well under makeup. Hydrogel may be light, but it\'s also mighty. Hyaluronic Acid, Squalane, and bark extracts hydrate the skin while b-silk™ protein delivers long-term firming, visible lifting, and increased elasticity over time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How does Hydrogel do it? If you’ve read our <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/rich-cream-deep-dive/\">Deep Dive on Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>, you know that b-silk™ protein works to reinforce the skin barrier, leading to healthy, radiant skin. Here\'s a refresher course on the skin barrier. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What is the skin barrier?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also known as the stratum corneum, the skin barrier is the skin\'s outermost layer. Its structure is similar to a brick wall, with old skin cells (a.k.a. corneocytes) stacked and held together by lipids and fats.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A healthy skin barrier performs two functions. First, it helps your skin retain moisture by preventing water loss from deeper skin layers. Second, it helps protect your skin from harsh elements like UV rays, pollutants, microbes, and chemicals.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your barrier’s function is a direct result of many factors, including nutrition, age, your daily skincare routine, and your surrounding environment. Over time, the barrier starts degrading and gets weaker and a little worse at performing its function. This brings on moisture loss, and lets in external aggravators, which further damage the deeper layers of skin by breaking down structural proteins like collagen and elastin. To further complicate matters, every time you cleanse, fats and lipids are stripped from the skin, weakening the skin’s barrier function.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":430} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1359.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-430\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Where does Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer come in?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein, our innovative key ingredient, mimics your natural barrier function and provides a breathable layer of reinforcement against the elements. Natural lipids and fats replenish your skin barrier, anti-inflammatory ingredients calm your skin, while active oils stimulate cell turnover and work to fight signs of aging.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While b-silk™ protein is doing its work, Hyaluronic Acid, Squalane, and bark extracts deliver hydration, for skin that feels plumper and healthier. As <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> is lightweight and refreshing, it can be worn day or night, on its own, or layered under makeup and SPF.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":431} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0167.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-431\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">What’s Inside?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">B-silk™ protein</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our proprietary ingredient forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that locks moisture in and keeps environmental factors at bay. When b-silk™ protein is applied, tiny silk molecules lock together to form an invisible film on the surface of your skin. Unlike many other barrier-forming ingredients, the b-silk™ protein barrier is not greasy and allows your skin to perform its function while providing vital reinforcement. Read more about <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-b-silk-protein/\">b-silk™ protein here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Hyaluronic Acid</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hyaluronic Acid (HA) is another powerful humectant found in the skin’s Natural Moisturizing Factor. And we mean powerful – HA can hold approximately 1,000 times its weight in water. HA works like a magnet to hold moisture, helping your skin look hydrated and healthy. When our skin is more hydrated, it appears plumper and fine lines are less visible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Squalane</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Squalane is a derivative of Squalene, a natural component of human skin. You may have also heard that Squalene comes from shark livers. Shark liver is a good source of Squalene, but we source our Squalene from a sustainable lab across the street from our labs in California. They produce Squalene through a vegan fermentation process. We are born with Squalene – it\'s one of the reasons babies have such glowing skin – but skin loses it over time. Squalane is a non-greasy oil that acts as an emollient, getting into the gaps between skin cells to make skin feel smoother.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Bark Extracts</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> contains natural bark extracts from four Boreal tree species: Acer Rubrum (Red Maple), Betula Alleghaniensis (Golden Birch), Picea Mariana (Black Spruce), Pinus Banksiana (Jack Pine) Bark Extract. These active ingredients deliver a boost of hydration that feels instantly refreshing, maintains long-lasting hydration, and works to improve skin elasticity over time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Let’s See the Results.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein is clinically shown to deliver results in just four weeks. With continued use, skin keeps getting better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Want to see for yourself? <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Shop Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> today to get started.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":278} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts4-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-278\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":281} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DataCharts8-Weeks-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-281\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Deep Dive: Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer','Our Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer is a refreshing gel that delivers hydrating ingredients and a punch of b-silk™ protein. Want to learn how it works? Great – we can talk about Hydrogel all day.','publish','closed','closed','','deep-dive-revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer','','','2019-09-05 15:14:33','2019-09-05 15:14:33','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=428',0,'post','',0),(413,3,'2019-08-11 14:31:26','2019-08-11 14:31:26','','eighteenb-camille-3070','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3070','','','2019-08-11 14:31:26','2019-08-11 14:31:26','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3070.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(414,3,'2019-08-11 14:31:29','2019-08-11 14:31:29','','eighteenb-camille-3300','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3300','','','2019-08-11 14:31:29','2019-08-11 14:31:29','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3300.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(415,3,'2019-08-11 14:31:32','2019-08-11 14:31:32','','eighteenb-camille-3319','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3319','','','2019-08-11 14:31:32','2019-08-11 14:31:32','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3319.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(416,3,'2019-08-11 14:31:36','2019-08-11 14:31:36','','eighteenb-camille-3324','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-camille-3324','','','2019-08-11 14:31:36','2019-08-11 14:31:36','',409,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/eighteenb-camille-3324.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(430,3,'2019-08-12 07:55:45','2019-08-12 07:55:45','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1359','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1359','','','2019-08-12 07:55:45','2019-08-12 07:55:45','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1359.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(431,3,'2019-08-12 07:55:59','2019-08-12 07:55:59','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0167','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0167','','','2019-08-12 07:55:59','2019-08-12 07:55:59','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0167.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(432,3,'2019-08-12 07:56:12','2019-08-12 07:56:12','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0092','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0092','','','2019-08-12 07:56:12','2019-08-12 07:56:12','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0092.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(433,3,'2019-08-12 07:56:20','2019-08-12 07:56:20','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0056','','','2019-08-12 07:56:20','2019-08-12 07:56:20','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(434,3,'2019-08-12 07:56:30','2019-08-12 07:56:30','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0353','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0353','','','2019-08-12 07:56:30','2019-08-12 07:56:30','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0353.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(435,3,'2019-08-12 08:04:36','2019-08-12 08:04:36','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0056-2','','','2019-08-12 08:04:36','2019-08-12 08:04:36','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(436,3,'2019-08-12 08:12:46','2019-08-12 08:12:46','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0056-3','','','2019-08-12 08:12:46','2019-08-12 08:12:46','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0056-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(437,3,'2019-08-12 08:15:59','2019-08-12 08:15:59','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0035','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0035','','','2019-08-12 08:15:59','2019-08-12 08:15:59','',428,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0035.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(473,3,'2019-08-29 12:37:44','2019-08-29 12:37:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Eighteen B just launched our third product, Firm + Replenish Serum. We asked Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, for her inspiration behind the formulation. Hint: It goes back to protecting skin’s natural barrier. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why did we decide to make a serum? The story goes back to the basics – protecting your skin’s natural barrier function.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here’s something you already know: your skin is a barrier between you and the world. For your skin to look and feel healthy, that barrier needs to stay healthy. However, many of the products we currently use, especially alkaline cleansers, are quite harsh and can break down the natural skin barrier. This can lead to sensitive skin, psoriasis, acne, and more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The concept of protecting the skin barrier may sound new – the<em> </em><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/30/style/all-of-those-products-are-making-your-skin-worse.html\"><em>New York Times</em></a><em> </em>just called “barrier protection” a beauty buzzword – but the skin barrier is far from a fad. Focusing on the skin barrier has been a long time coming. It’s why we created b-silk™ protein.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":476} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1832.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-476\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B-silk™ protein, our proprietary ingredient, is a dual-action, lightweight barrier that replenishes your skin’s vital barrier function. It leaves your skin soft and smooth while visibly firming, lifting, and increasing overall radiance. (<a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-b-silk-protein/\">Read more about b-silk™ protein here</a>.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We launched Eighteen B with two products: <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer/\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> and <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream/\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>. Both moisturizers were designed to hydrate the skin and support the barrier function. However, we knew there was a first step that would allow the skin to reap more benefits from our b-silk™ protein. We could replenish our skin’s natural barrier before adding our hydrating ingredients.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In our research, it became clear that one of the most disruptive things we do to our skin’s natural barrier is to cleanse and exfoliate. Cleansing is essential to healthy skin, of course, but it’s important to replenish those healthy ingredients you just stripped away. What could instantly replenish that barrier? You guessed it: a serum.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":475} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1814.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-475\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we were developing our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a>, the serums I saw on the market delivered a potent dose of great ingredients, like Vitamin C and Vitamin A. However, none of these serums worked to replenish our Natural Moisturizing Factor and essential Lipids, which our skin loses during cleansing.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF) is a cocktail of Amino Acids, PCA, Hyaluronic Acid, and more that the skin naturally creates to keep the stratum corneum and epidermis hydrated. Our Serum features a potent dose of NMF so your skin doesn’t need to work so hard to replenish NMF on its own. That means the skin is in a better state to function normally, and isn’t using up precious biological resources to maintain a healthy state. B-silk™ protein works to lock in these ingredients so they can do their  replenishing work. That was our goal: to repair the skin’s natural barrier before we apply our moisturizer.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Dr. Shari Marchbein said in the <em><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/30/style/all-of-those-products-are-making-your-skin-worse.html\">New York Times</a></em> story, “If you frost a dry cake, the cake is still dry. If you frost a moist cake, it stays moist.” We completely agree. We\'ve always felt our moisturizers were icing on the cake.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions for Lindsay? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ask Lindsay: Why We Created a Serum','Why did we decide to make a serum? We asked Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, for her inspiration behind the formulation. Hint: the story goes back to the basics – protecting your skin’s natural barrier function. ','publish','open','open','','ask-lindsay-why-we-created-a-serum','','','2019-09-10 10:03:14','2019-09-10 10:03:14','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=473',0,'post','',0),(442,3,'2019-08-18 08:09:10','2019-08-18 08:09:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>This week, we hosted an intimate dinner in New York with chef and <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-woman-camille-becerra/\">Eighteen B Woman, Camille Becerra</a>, who works mostly with sustainable, vegan ingredients. We wanted to learn even more about how our food affects our skin, so we asked a nutritionist exactly what we should be eating. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At Eighteen B, we believe that healthy skin comes from the inside-out and the outside-in. Eating fresh, whole foods is always a great place to start, of course, but we wanted to learn which foods work the hardest for skin health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jennifer Cholewka, RD, CNSC, CDN, is an advanced clinical nutrition coordinator at <a href=\"https://www.mountsinai.org/\">The Mount Sinai Hospital of Manhattan</a>. She talked to us about the vitamins and nutrients she recommends to make our skin glow.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Vitamin C&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":452} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/shutterstock_1302884467.jpg\" alt=\"Food for healthy skin - Papaya\" class=\"wp-image-452\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vitamin C is a buzzy ingredient in skincare treatments, but it works wonders from the inside, too. How? Vitamin C promotes the growth and repair of all tissues in the body. \"Vitamin C is a necessary component for the growth of collagen,\" Jennifer told us. \"Collagen provides elasticity, integrity, and firmness to our skin.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What are the best foods for Vitamin C? Colorful fruits like guava, strawberries, kiwi, and oranges all have more than 100% daily value (DV) per cup. Papaya and broccoli deliver more than 90% DV of Vitamin C per cup. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Omega-3 Fatty Acids</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":454} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/shutterstock_766161868.jpg\" alt=\"Food for healthy skin - Walnuts\" class=\"wp-image-454\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Really want your skin to shine? Start with the good fats. Omega-3 Fatty Acids area are a much-touted superfood, with benefits that range from heart health to mental health. These multitasking fats promote glowing skin, too. \"Omega 3 Fatty Acids possess powerful anti-inflammatory properties. These fats protect skin cells from sun damage and alter how our bodies respond to UV rays, minimizing the aging effects of sun exposure.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Where to find Omega-3s? Jennifer tells us, \"cold water fatty fish such as salmon, mackerel, tuna, herring, and sardines.\" For vegetarians, \"try plant-based sources like chia seeds, flax seed, walnuts, and plant oils like canola and flax seed oil.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Vitamin E&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":451} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Sunflower-Seeds.jpg\" alt=\"Food for healthy skin - Sunflower seeds\" class=\"wp-image-451\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here\'s another case for eating plenty of nuts. \"Vitamin E functions as an antioxidant, protecting body tissue from free radicals. Free radicals contribute to cellular damage, which expedites the skin aging process.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nuts and seeds deliver the richest amounts of Vitamin E. The very best source is is wheat germ oil (one tablespoon exceeds 100% DV). However, Jennifer admits that wheat germ oil isn\'t necessarily an everyday ingredient. \"More commonly consumed sources include sunflower seeds and sunflower oil (66% DV per ounce, 37% DV per tablespoon), almonds and almond oil (48% DV per ounce, 36% DV per tablespoon), and hazelnuts and hazelnut oil (28% DV per ounce, 43% DV per tablespoon).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Vitamin A</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":453} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/shutterstock_343379489.jpg\" alt=\"Food for healthy skin - Sweet potatoes\" class=\"wp-image-453\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To keep fighting free radicals, don\'t skimp on the Vitamin A. \"Free radicals break down collagen and increase our sensitivity to the sun,\" Jennifer says. Vitamin A fights those free radicals. \"Vitamin A decreases hyper-pigmentation and inflammation associated with prolonged sun exposure.\" (But that doesn\'t mean you can bypass the sunscreen!) That\'s not all: \"Vitamin A stimulates cell production and growth, specifically fibroblasts, which are responsible for keeping skin firm and youthful.\" </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Plant sources that are rich in Vitamin A – all with more than 100% DV per serving – include sweet potatoes, carrots, spinach, and butternut squash. Tuna is one of the top sources of Vitamin A, with 143% DV per serving.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have a question for our skincare experts? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ask our Experts: Superfoods for Glowing Skin','We believe that healthy skin comes from the inside-out and the outside-in. We wanted to learn more about how food affects our skin, so we asked a nutritionist exactly what vitamins and nutrients we should be eating.','publish','open','open','','foods-for-healthy-glowing-skin','','','2019-08-22 14:32:18','2019-08-22 14:32:18','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=442',0,'post','',0),(558,4,'2019-10-24 18:25:40','2019-10-24 18:25:40','','20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1832','','inherit','open','closed','','20190727_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1832-3','','','2019-10-24 18:25:40','2019-10-24 18:25:40','',552,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/20190727_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1832.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(561,3,'2019-11-01 10:57:53','2019-11-01 10:57:53','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Are you loving our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=18bw_bj\">holiday sets</a>? We are, too. It\'s one of the many reasons we\'re grateful for Brittany Jepsen, the founder and creative director of <a href=\"https://thehousethatlarsbuilt.com/\">The House That Lars Built</a>, the creative services company behind the design. We talked to Brittany, our newest Eighteen B Woman, about crafting, creativity, and the joy of paying gratitude forward.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Brittany Jepsen has a gift of taking everyday objects and making them joyful. Take a look at her award-winning website, <a href=\"https://thehousethatlarsbuilt.com/\">The House That Lars Built</a>, and you\'ll see what we mean. With a clever twirl and some fishing line, a piece of rope becomes a purse. A stack of plates becomes a one-of-a-kind light fixture. Crimson crepe paper blossoms into a fluffy peony. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Brittany believes that gifts should be shared (and not just because it\'s the holidays). She launched The House That Lars Built 11 years ago as her personal portfolio. Today, it\'s grown into a creative services company with six employees, an internship program, and more than 190,000 followers on Instagram. \"Our mission is to provide people with the tools and confidence to make projects and learn how to make their lives more artful.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":570} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Women-Brittany-Jepsen-The-House-That-Lars-Built-3477.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-570\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Artful living\" may sound intimidating to the less crafty among us, but have no fear: Brittany believes the process is just as meaningful as the finished product. \"\'Artful\' is our way of saying that what you surround yourself with and how you spend your time should be thoughtful and meaningful. If you do, you’ll live a more beautiful life,” Brittany says. “I find that everyone can benefit from making things with their hands, in whatever capacity that speaks to them most.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a world where anything can be delivered to your door in two days, Brittany has built an audience that craves something real and handmade. “I believe that the more we become sucked into our phones and other technologies, the more we need something tangible to hold on to, to rest our eyes, and delve into a new world of creation and problem solving.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":572} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Women-Brittany-Jepsen-The-House-That-Lars-Built-3353.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-572\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We asked The House That Lars Built to design our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=18bw_bj\">holiday collection</a> because we love how whimsical and personal their pieces are. And our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=18bw_bj\">holiday collection</a>, inspired by gratitude, is personal to us. We are filled with gratitude as we look back on the past year. We made scientific advances, launched three products, and built an incredible team, all because our customers made it possible. While we have a lot of ground to cover yet – stay tuned for exciting updates in 2020! – we want to pause to share our gratitude with you, the ones who made it happen. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=18bw_bj\">Shop Eighteen B holiday gift sets now.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Brittany\'s design was inspired by her own gratitude. \"The Eighteen B holiday design comes from a DIY project of a painted nativity set inspired by a set my mom made when she was young. We took elements from the time of her youth and translated them into a holiday scheme. My mother is my kindred spirit in so many ways and I can’t help but be grateful for her influence in my life. Conveying that gratitude was the perfect way to capture this message.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":574} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Product-x-The-House-That-Lars-Built-4883-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-574\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s not just the pretty packaging – Brittany designed a gratitude notepad to come with each holiday set. “I remember hearing advice about noting what I’m grateful for each morning and reviewing it at night. It’s really helped me shift my focus to what’s important.\" </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for what Brittany is grateful for, she says, “so much! Everything from big picture stuff – the earth, flowers, beautiful architecture, my work to small stuff. I’m absolutely most grateful for my little family. My son, Jasper, is a year and a half and the most chubby, lovable squeeze there is. He entertains me and warms my heart so much.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":573} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Women-Brittany-Jepsen-The-House-That-Lars-Built-3317.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-573\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We were thrilled to hear that Brittany\'s skin is feeling grateful, too. \"Since I started using the products I\'ve received more compliments on my skin than I have since high school! My makeup doesn\'t flake off and it feels fresh. I haven\'t felt this way in a long time!\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"My absolute favorite is the <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=ss_richcream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>. It\'s super dry here in Utah and it\'s done not great things for my skin. The cream has been essential for making my makeup go on smoothly. It\'s a new essential!\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Brittany told us, \"There’s no better way to communicate gratitude than to continue it by paying it forward.\" In that spirit, we hope you share the gift of glowing skin this season. It will help us all shine a little brighter. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Eighteen B Woman: Brittany Jepsen of The House That Lars Built','We talked to Brittany Jepsen, the creative director of The House That Lars Built and our newest Eighteen B Woman, about crafting, creativity, and the joy of paying gratitude forward.','publish','open','open','','eighteen-b-woman-brittany-jepsen','','','2019-12-11 16:39:08','2019-12-11 16:39:08','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=561',0,'post','',0),(569,3,'2019-10-29 12:59:47','2019-10-29 12:59:47','','EighteenB Women - Brittany Jepsen - The House That Lars Built-3219','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-women-brittany-jepsen-the-house-that-lars-built-3219','','','2019-10-29 12:59:47','2019-10-29 12:59:47','',561,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2