,'closed','','eighteenb-product9','','','2019-10-30 14:07:15','2019-10-30 14:07:15','',575,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Product9.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(590,3,'2019-10-30 14:12:32','2019-10-30 14:12:32','','EighteenB-Product5','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-product5','','','2019-10-30 14:12:32','2019-10-30 14:12:32','',575,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Product5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(591,3,'2019-10-31 14:35:45','2019-10-31 14:35:45','','TheLabHolidayBanner_3','','inherit','open','closed','','thelabholidaybanner_3','','','2019-10-31 14:35:45','2019-10-31 14:35:45','',115,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/TheLabHolidayBanner_3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(593,3,'2019-10-31 14:54:39','2019-10-31 14:54:39','','EighteenB Product','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-product-3','','','2019-10-31 14:54:39','2019-10-31 14:54:39','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/EighteenB-Product-x-The-House-That-Lars-Built-4951.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(597,3,'2019-11-07 10:12:54','2019-11-07 10:12:54','','TheLabHolidayBanner_V3','','inherit','open','closed','','thelabholidaybanner_v3','','','2019-11-07 10:12:54','2019-11-07 10:12:54','',115,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/TheLabHolidayBanner_V3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(599,3,'2019-11-07 10:14:20','2019-11-07 10:14:20','','TheLabHolidayBanner_V2','','inherit','open','closed','','thelabholidaybanner_v2','','','2019-11-07 10:14:20','2019-11-07 10:14:20','',115,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/TheLabHolidayBanner_V2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(600,3,'2019-11-07 14:59:48','2019-11-07 14:59:48','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>You might be surprised to hear that dry skin and dehydrated skin are two different skincare concerns. Here\'s how they differ, how to tell if your skin is dehydrated, and how to make it glow.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dry and dehydrated skin may sound interchangeable, but they\'re two very different concerns. Dry skin is a skin type, meaning skin that has fewer oil-producing glands. Dehydrated skin is a temporary condition, meaning skin that is lacking water. In fact, it’s possible to have dehydrated skin that is still oily. It\'s confusing, but true!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While we can\'t change our oil glands, we do have the power to change how much water is in our skin. Dehydrated skin is mostly caused by environmental factors, like cold weather, dry climates, food choices, and caffeine and alcohol consumption.&nbsp;That means we can keep our skin hydrated through better choices and better skincare. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Is your skin dry or dehydrated?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How can you tell? Here\'s a quick test. Take a look in the mirror and gently pinch the skin on your forehead. Is the skin shiny and crinkling into tiny lines? That means it\'s probably dehydrated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Skin is particularly prone to dehydration in the colder months. Cold weather brings dry air, which can pull moisture from the skin. This can cause a host of skin concerns, including dullness, itchiness, dark circles under the eyes, and more visible wrinkles. That means if you wake up to wrinkles you don’t recognize, chances are good your skin is just dehydrated.&nbsp;Here\'s how to fix it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Read more about protecting your skin in cool weather here: </strong></em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/5-ingredients-your-skin-needs-this-fall/\"><em><strong>5 Ingredients Your Skin Needs This Fall</strong></em></a><em><strong>.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Here\'s how to combat dehydrated skin</strong>. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">Step one: Hydrate</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your skin is showing signs of dehydration, the first thing to do is drink a glass of water. Have you been drinking caffeine or alcohol? Make it two glasses of water. We hate to be the bearer of bad news, but both caffeine and alcohol dehydrate the skin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">Step two: Exfoliate</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wash away dull, dry skin with a gentle exfoliator. For gentle daily exfoliation, try washing your face with a muslin cloth. (We particularly like <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Karlling-Cotton-Facial-Cleansing-Muslin/dp/B00IBFC874/ref=sr_1_1_sspa?keywords=muslin+cloth+for+face&amp;qid=1574181182&amp;sr=8-1-spons&amp;psc=1&amp;spLa=ZW5jcnlwdGVkUXVhbGlmaWVyPUFCVkdYMEc1MktFNkYmZW5jcnlwdGVkSWQ9QTAyNDQ5OTgzSURDUUpDQVJEWElHJmVuY3J5cHRlZEFkSWQ9QTA0NzE2MDlPMlBYUU1IV0dVTlgmd2lkZ2V0TmFtZT1zcF9hdGYmYWN0aW9uPWNsaWNrUmVkaXJlY3QmZG9Ob3RMb2dDbGljaz10cnVl\">these muslins by Karlling</a>.) Once a week, use an exfoliating scrub for a more vigorous buff. Here\'s a DIY solution good enough to eat: Try mixing some white sugar with coconut oil.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">Step three: Replenish with Serum</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, it’s time to put your skincare to work. Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> was designed to replenish your skin’s Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF) after cleansing and exfoliating. Your NMF is a cocktail of Amino Acids, PCA, Hyaluronic Acid, and more that the skin naturally creates to keep the skin barrier hydrated. Our Serum delivers a potent dose of NMF so your skin doesn’t need to work so hard to replenish these ingredients on its own.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">Step four: Lock in the Moisture</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, double down on the moisturizer. The most effective way to combat dehydrated skin topically is to use a moisturizer that is rich in humectants. Humectants are molecules that act like a magnet, drawing moisture to the skin. One of the most powerful humectants is Hyaluronic Acid (HA), found in our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a> and <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> (and our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a>, at that).&nbsp;As an at-home hack, especially in the cooler months, you can supercharge your HA by sleeping with a humidifier. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Read how to get the most out of your moisturizer here: </strong></em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/apply-moisturizer/\"><em><strong>There’s a Right Way to Apply Moisturizer</strong></em></a><em><strong>.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the weather is cool, many dermatologists recommend using a richer moisturizer before bed. As New York-based dermatologist Dr. Ross C. Radusky told <em><a href=\"https://www.allure.com/story/dry-vs-dehydrated-skin-whats-the-difference?irclickid=R8W1xuRGKxyJRcewUx0Mo382UknwJGQhC1KYyU0&amp;source=ALB_AFF_IMPACT_adgoal%20GmbH&amp;utm_source=Impact-affiliate&amp;utm_campaign=Online%20Tracking%20Link&amp;utm_medium=adgoal%20GmbH&amp;irgwc=1\">Allure</a></em>, \"Even though we\'re shielded from the harsh outdoor climate, heated dry air causes us to naturally lose moisture while we sleep.\" Our deeply nourishing <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> is the perfect moisturizer for the job, packed with hydrating Ceramides, Squalane, and Gentianaceae Leaf Extract.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you\'re moisturizing with Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream or Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer, our proprietary b-silk™&nbsp;protein forms a lightweight barrier that locks hydrating ingredients close to the skin. After four weeks, b-silk™&nbsp;protein is clinically shown to make skin more hydrated. We\'ll toast to that (with a tall glass of water, of course). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Is Your Skin Dry or Just Dehydrated? Here\'s How to Tell the Difference.','Dry and dehydrated skin may sound interchangeable, but they\'re two different concerns. Here\'s the difference, how to tell if your skin is dehydrated, and how to make it glow.','publish','open','open','','is-your-skin-dry-or-dehydrated','','','2019-11-20 18:56:46','2019-11-20 18:56:46','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=600',0,'post','',0),(601,3,'2019-11-07 13:09:52','2019-11-07 13:09:52','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0859','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_0859','','','2019-11-07 13:09:52','2019-11-07 13:09:52','',600,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_0859.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(605,3,'2019-11-11 16:27:13','2019-11-11 16:27:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>We\'ve dedicated the holidays at Eighteen B to gratitude and the joy of paying it forward. In that spirit, we\'ve teamed up with <a href=\"https://thehousethatlarsbuilt.com/\">The House That Lars Built</a>, the design team behind our beautiful holiday sets, to support Nest, a nonprofit that supports the handworker economy. Here\'s why.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Founded in 2006, <a href=\"http://buildanest.org\">Nest</a> is a nonprofit dedicated to building a new handworker economy to generate global workforce inclusivity, improve women’s wellbeing beyond factories, and preserve cultural traditions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nest works closely with brands, philanthropists, and artisan businesses to promote handworkers. With radical transparency, data-driven development, and fair market access, they connect craftspeople, brands, and consumers in a value chain that creates beautiful things and improves workers\' lives. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":617} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/nest_13521803_Full.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-617\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.buildanest.org/\">Nest</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We at Eighteen B, a woman-founded business, believe in building up women in business. But it\'s more than that: as scientists, we care deeply about taking the time to create a product with care. As a sustainable business, we care about keeping responsibility and ethics at the forefront. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Nest cause is close Brittany Jepsen\'s heart – our newest <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-woman-brittany-jepsen/\">Eighteen B Woman</a> – for these reasons and more. As the creative director of an award-winning DIY blog, Brittany Jepsen is a major proponent of the handmade. When she came across Nest, she knew is was the right fit. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-woman-brittany-jepsen/\">Read our Eighteen B Woman profile of Brittany here.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Brittany told us, \"The moment I first heard about Nest, I knew it was an organization that I wanted to be affiliated with. My mission at <a href=\"https://thehousethatlarsbuilt.com/\">The House That Lars Built</a> is to provide tools to people to create a beautiful life. Nest aligns perfectly with that mission.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":620} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/nest_20483582.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-620\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.buildanest.org/\">Nest</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She also believes in preserving crafts throughout the world. \"I\'ve had the chance myself to visit some beautiful places to help preserve such cherished identities. We cannot let the beautiful traditions of the world pass on without acknowledging them and lifting them into view,” she told us. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I\'m also a big supporter of highlighting working women and the improvement of their conditions and elevation of their status. Craft-based work is the second largest employer of women throughout the world, so it\'s only right to highlight their great work. If I can be even a small voice in bringing awareness to this mission, then I will consider my work a success.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mark your calendars: on Giving Tuesday (December 3) we\'re donating $5 from each order to the hardworking women of Nest. We\'re grateful to Brittany for introducing us to the team at Nest and, above all, we\'re grateful to you for paying it forward. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>P.S. Do you have an incredible, inspiring friend in your life? We want to meet her. We\'re taking nominations for our next Eighteen B Woman. Send us your nominations at this <a href=\"https://forms.gle/hzxndyGcTtoJ5gBM7\">link</a> through</em></strong><em><strong> Friday, November 15.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Paying It Forward: Why We Support Nest this Giving Tuesday','In the spirit of gratitude and paying it forward, we\'ve teamed up with The House That Lars Built, the design team behind our holiday sets, to support Nest, a nonprofit that supports the handworker economy. Here\'s why.','publish','open','open','','giving-tuesday-nest','','','2019-11-11 16:54:02','2019-11-11 16:54:02','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=605',0,'post','',0),(606,3,'2019-11-19 10:55:17','2019-11-19 10:55:17','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Is your holiday shopping underway?  To help you prep for shopping season, we\'ve assembled a gift guide series to highlight our favorite products, brands, and causes. Our first gift guide is dedicated to the textile we treasure most: silk.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'re launching the Eighteen B gift guide series with a roundup inspired by <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/why-b-silk-protein-belongs-in-your-skincare-regimen/\">b-silk™&nbsp;protein</a>, our revolutionary key ingredient. Silk feels like a true indulgence – so much so that we may not buy it for ourselves. This holiday season, let\'s lean into the luxurious, shall we? Treat yourself or your lived ones to something special something special. Here are the silky products we\'re eyeing at Eighteen B HQ.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=silk_gg\">Shop Eighteen B holiday sets here.</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">1. Mulberry Silk Pillowcase from Brooklinen</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":622} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/ivory-silk-pillowcase_detail_1200x.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-622\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Silk works wonders on the skin, and not just in your skincare. While cotton pillowcases stick and form creases on the skin while we sleep, silk pillowcases naturally slip and glide. That means there\'s less breakage on the hair and less creasing on the skin. A particularly luxurious choice is the <a href=\"https://www.brooklinen.com/products/mulberry-silk-pillowcase\">Mulberry Silk Pillowcase from Brooklinen</a>. Now, that\'s what we call beauty sleep.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">2. Silk Cashmere Turtleneck from Nadaam</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":611} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Nadaam-Silk-Cashmere.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-611\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When it comes to coveted textiles, <a href=\"https://naadam.co/products/silk-cashmere-ribbed-turtleneck-black?variant=12440583012469\">Silk Cashmere Turtleneck from Nadaam</a> is blends the best of both worlds: lustrous silk and cuddly cashmere. We particularly love that Nadaam uses silk from pesticide-free silkworm cocoons and cashmere that\'s ethically sourced. At 85% silk and 15% cashmere, it doesn\'t get much cozier. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">3. Silk Hair Wrap from Silke</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":609} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Silke-The-Poppy.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-609\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.silkelondon.com/collections/shop-the-collection/products/the-poppy-silke-silk-hair-wrap\">Silke</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This glamorous wrap isn\'t just for looks – it\'s made from 100% mulberry silk to protect your hair while you sleep. All that tossing and turning causes friction, which leads to frizz, split ends, dryness, and bed head. We particularly love the vibrant colors of <a href=\"https://www.silkelondon.com/collections/shop-the-collection/products/the-poppy-silke-silk-hair-wrap\">The Poppy</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">4. Washable Silk Robe from Lunya</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":610} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Washable-Silk-Robe-Lunya.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-610\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.lunya.co/collections/washable-silk/products/washable-silk-robe?variant=16146116313131\">Lunya</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We thought the <a href=\"https://www.lunya.co/collections/washable-silk/products/washable-silk-robe?variant=16146116313131\">Washable Silk Robe by Lunya</a> was almost too pretty for the living room, but Lunya disagrees: \"We believe that staying in is the new going out, so we designed the dream robe for your dream night – binging Netflix, drinking wine, and going to bed by 10.\" With washable silk, you can look like a goddess without the trips to the dry cleaner. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">5. slipsilk™ Sleep Mask from Slip</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":623} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/SLIP_BerryKiss_SM_ShotA_820x_a0595a8e-6d49-4337-95ff-8f53935a9044_820x.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-623\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.slip.com/\">Slip</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The properties that make silk perfect for a pillowcase make it an ideal eye mask, too. The <a href=\"https://www.slip.com/collections/new-2/products/sleep-mask-berry-kiss\">Sleep Mask from Slip</a> is consistently rated among the best eye masks on the market. Their proprietary Slipsilk™ provides the ultimate blend of softness, durability, shine, and thickness. Sleep Masks are 100% silk, including the filler. Pair that with our <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/why-b-silk-protein-belongs-in-your-skincare-regimen/\">b-silk™&nbsp;protein</a>-powered regimen, and you\'ll wake up to skin that\'s silky smooth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">6. Tarragon Dress from Dôen</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":613} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Doen-Dress.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-613\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://shopdoen.com/products/tarragon-dress-black?_pos=2&amp;_sid=0ac73d3c0&amp;_ss=r\">Doen</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A dreamy gift for a friend (or yourself), <a href=\"https://shopdoen.com/products/tarragon-dress-black\">Tarragon Dress by Dôen</a> would be equally at home at a Spanish villa, a friend\'s wedding or a walk in the park. Based in Los Angeles, Dôen is a collective of creative female designers. They are committed to working with woman-owned and -run factories whenever possible. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">7. Silk Marina Pajamas from Sleepy Jones</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":624} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Sleepy-Jones.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-624\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'re loving the cheeky <a href=\"https://shop.sleepyjones.com/products/silk-marina-pajama-shirt-19\">Silk Marina Pajamas</a> by Sleepy Jones. Peppered with polka dots, this set has far more personality than your go-to t-shirt and shorts. As Sleepy Jones says, \"We think you should take your pleasure seriously.\" We happen to agree. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Eighteen B Holiday Gift Guide: Silk Products on our Wish List','To help you prepare for shopping season, we\'ve assembled a gift guide series to highlight our favorite products, brands, and causes. Our first gift guide is dedicated to the textile 