Full','','inherit','open','closed','','nest_13521803_full','','','2019-11-10 19:56:07','2019-11-10 19:56:07','',605,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/nest_13521803_Full.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(618,3,'2019-11-10 19:58:44','2019-11-10 19:58:44','','nest_94615773','','inherit','open','closed','','nest_94615773','','','2019-11-10 19:58:44','2019-11-10 19:58:44','',605,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/nest_94615773.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(620,3,'2019-11-11 16:32:58','2019-11-11 16:32:58','','nest_20483582','','inherit','open','closed','','nest_20483582','','','2019-11-11 16:32:58','2019-11-11 16:32:58','',605,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/nest_20483582.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(622,3,'2019-11-19 09:54:55','2019-11-19 09:54:55','','ivory-silk-pillowcase_detail_1200x','','inherit','open','closed','','ivory-silk-pillowcase_detail_1200x','','','2019-11-19 09:54:55','2019-11-19 09:54:55','',606,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/ivory-silk-pillowcase_detail_1200x.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(624,3,'2019-11-19 10:47:51','2019-11-19 10:47:51','','Sleepy Jones','','inherit','open','closed','','sleepy-jones','','','2019-11-19 10:47:51','2019-11-19 10:47:51','',606,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Sleepy-Jones.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(630,3,'2019-11-22 12:01:13','2019-11-22 12:01:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, is a proud recipient of ELLE\'s 2019 Future of Beauty Award. We talked to Lindsay about what the award means to her and how she\'s working to change the industry one ingredient at a time. We\'re so proud!</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This year, ELLE published its first-ever <a href=\"https://www.elle.com/beauty/a29758493/future-of-beauty-awards-2019/\">Future of Beauty Awards</a>, honoring the most exciting innovations in the beauty industry. We are proud to announce that our very own Lindsay Wray, Chief Science Officer, was among the 2019 winners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Future of Beauty Awards honor innovations in skincare products, haircare products, makeup, and body treatments, as well as the founders behind industry-shaking companies. Here\'s what ELLE had to say about Lindsay and Eighteen B:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>“Lindsay Wray, chief science officer at Eighteen B, developed the first-ever biodegradable vegan silk, which has regenerative properties and helps improve skin’s elasticity. She champions sustainability by researching common skin-care ingredients to determine their environmental impact and how to replace the harmful ones, like liquid plastics, with greener alternatives.\"</strong></em> - <a href=\"https://www.elle.com/beauty/a29758493/future-of-beauty-awards-2019/\">ELLE</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":632} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/IMG_9402.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-632\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lindsay says, \"I am truly honored to get this award. I have a lot of respect for the people at ELLE and am so glad the feeling is mutual.&nbsp;I think the meaning of this award is much bigger than myself. I think this award signifies an important shift in the beauty world in two ways. One: the beauty consumer wants to talk about skin care and skin health in a transparent and scientific way. Two: sustainable, vegan, and clean beauty is here to stay.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Eighteen B team was particularly thrilled to see Lindsay\'s environmental research highlighted. Lindsay puts an impressive amount of time and energy into researching each ingredient\'s toxicology profile. When data is tough to interpret, we hire trained toxicologists to assist. If the data can\'t be found, she makes contact with the vendors to get answers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Lindsay puts it, \"This takes a lot of time and energy but the result is high confidence in our ingredient lists – no fear mongering, no regrettable substitutions.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/ask-lindsay-why-we-decided-not-to-use-silicones-in-our-products/\">Read Ask Lindsay: Why We Decided Not to Use Silicones in Our Products</a></strong></em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/ask-lindsay-why-we-decided-not-to-use-silicones-in-our-products/\">.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for what the future of holds for Eighteen B, Lindsay has big plans. \"There are three things I hope to achieve with Eighteen B: (1) talk about skin care and skin health in a scientific and data-backed way; (2) bring solutions (not just raise awareness about problems) to the table, starting with our own proprietary ingredient b-silk™&nbsp;protein; and (3) formulate beautiful and effective products that you can\'t wait to put on everyday.\" Go get \'em, Lindsay! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">More Eighteen B In The News</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Forbes</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/celiashatzman/2019/11/18/holiday-gift-guide-2019-the-best-womens-skincare-products/#40c034554920\">Holiday Gift Guide 2019: The Best Women’s Skincare Products</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Zoe Report</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/celiashatzman/2019/11/18/holiday-gift-guide-2019-the-best-womens-skincare-products/#15772d674920\">The Oily Skin Routine To Live By, Even When It’s Cold Outside</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Perez Hilton: </strong><a href=\"https://perezhilton.com/dry-skin-moisturizers-foundations-2019/\">Save Your Dry Skin! Moisturizers &amp; Hydrating Foundations You’ll Want To Try!</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Lindsay Wray Wins ELLE\'s 2019 Future of Beauty Award','Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, won ELLE\'s 2019 Future of Beauty Award. We talked to Lindsay about what the award means to her and how she\'s working to change the industry one ingredient at a time. Go Linsday!','publish','open','open','','lindsay-wray-wins-elles-2019-future-of-beauty-award','','','2019-12-11 16:35:22','2019-12-11 16:35:22','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=630',0,'post','',0),(631,3,'2019-11-22 10:35:34','2019-11-22 10:35:34','','IMG_9368','','inherit','open','closed','','img_9368','','','2019-11-22 10:35:34','2019-11-22 10:35:34','',630,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/IMG_9368.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(632,3,'2019-11-22 10:54:04','2019-11-22 10:54:04','','IMG_9402','','inherit','open','closed','','img_9402','','','2019-11-22 10:54:04','2019-11-22 10:54:04','',630,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/IMG_9402.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(627,3,'2019-11-19 11:40:24','2019-11-19 11:40:24','','Eighteen B Lars Product Shots-8768','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteen-b-lars-product-shots-8768','','','2019-11-19 11:40:24','2019-11-19 11:40:24','',606,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Eighteen-B-Lars-Product-Shots-8768.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(651,3,'2019-12-03 15:21:26','2019-12-03 15:21:26','','eighteenb-wendy-0382','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-wendy-0382','','','2019-12-03 15:21:26','2019-12-03 15:21:26','',650,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/eighteenb-wendy-0382.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(652,3,'2019-12-05 12:34:11','2019-12-05 12:34:11','','Vegamour','','inherit','open','closed','','vegamour','','','2019-12-05 12:34:11','2019-12-05 12:34:11','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Vegamour.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(653,3,'2019-12-05 12:43:49','2019-12-05 12:43:49','','Vegamour','','inherit','open','closed','','vegamour-2','','','2019-12-05 12:43:49','2019-12-05 12:43:49','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Vegamour-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(649,3,'2019-11-28 10:17:47','2019-11-28 10:17:47','','RMS Beauty','','inherit','open','closed','','rms-beauty','','','2019-11-28 10:17:47','2019-11-28 10:17:47','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/RMS-Beauty.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(645,3,'2019-11-28 09:05:43','2019-11-28 09:05:43','','Alima Alchemy','','inherit','open','closed','','alima-alchemy','','','2019-11-28 09:05:43','2019-11-28 09:05:43','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Alima-Alchemy.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(650,3,'2019-12-03 15:53:37','2019-12-03 15:53:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Is your skin ready for winter? Even if you love the coziness of the cooler months, winter calls for a little more self care. Here are seven ways to take better care of your skin (and your soul) when the days turn cold.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before we go into the cold, let’s talk about why winter weather can be so hard on the skin. Cold air holds less moisture than warm air, so it feels very dry. Once we get inside to warm up, the assault continues: heaters and radiators also dry the air. This combination means our skin gets dehydrated easily.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s not just the skin that’s at risk. Roughly <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2686645/#s4title\">6% of Americans</a> suffer from Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD), a drop in mood due to the dark and cold days of winter. Even if we don’t have diagnosed SAD, it\'s common to feel a little blue in the winter. Here’s how to keep your skin glowing and your mood up even when the weather is working against you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>1. Exfoliate. Your skincare will work better.</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No matter the season, it\'s important to remove excess dead skin cells through exfoliation. When the excess cells are removed, skin appears healthier and more vibrant. But that\'s not all – skincare products are better absorbed on exfoliated skin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But be sure to go easy! Exfoliating too harshly can damage the skin barrier. A damaged skin barrier means skin can be easily irritated, which will feel particularly uncomfortable in the dry winter climate.&nbsp;(Read more about why a healthy skin barrier is so important <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/dermatologist-dr-tyler-hollmig-on-why-the-skin-barrier-is-key/\">here</a>.) <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>2. Replenish your skin barrier with a nourishing serum.&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your skin is far more vulnerable just after it\'s been scrubbed. Cleansing and exfoliating strip away your skin’s Natural Moisturizing Factor (NMF), the cocktail of hydrating components your skin naturally produces to keep itself hydrated. (<a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/what-is-natural-moisturizing-factor-nmf/\">Read more about NMF here</a>.)&nbsp;Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum/\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> delivers a dose of NMF so your skin doesn\'t need to work as hard to replenish it on its own. <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>3. Load up on the moisturizer.</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best way to keep your skin feeling healthy all winter long is to apply a liberal layer of moisturizer day and night. To make sure you’re getting the most out of your moisturizer, be sure it’s packed with humectants. Humectants act like a sponge, attracting water from the environment (and from the moisturizer) into the skin. One of the most powerful humectants is Hyaluronic Acid (HA), which can hold approximately 1,000 times its weight in water.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HA can be found in our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a>, <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/revitalizing-hydrogel-moisturizer\">Revitalizing Hydrogel Moisturizer</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream/\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>. To really put your humectants to work – and combat the dry air from your heater – we <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/5-ingredients-your-skin-needs-this-fall/\">often recommend</a> sleeping with a humidifier. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>4. Lock in that hard-earned moisture.</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that you\'ve moisturized, make sure those nourishing ingredients stay where you want them. Our b-silk™ protein forms a lightweight, breathable barrier that keeps hydrating ingredients close to the skin. It acts as a vital defense against environmental stressors as well as a moisture depot, delivering immediate and sustained hydration throughout the day. As shown in a clinical study, b-silk™ protein leaves your skin incredibly soft and smooth while visibly firming, lifting, and increasing overall radiance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=winter_skin\">For more than 35% off the full Eighteen B regimen, shop our limited edition holiday sets here. </a></em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>5. Wear your SPF</strong>.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We know you know this already, but it must be said: wear sunscreen! UV rays can be just as harmful in the winter as they are in the summer. In fact, those rays can be even stronger on a snowy day. Fresh snow is great at reflecting light, and can almost <a href=\"https://www.who.int/uv/faq/whatisuv/en/index3.html\">double your exposure</a> to UV rays. Don’t forget to apply to the tops of your hands as well, unless they’re wrapped in a pair of gloves.&nbsp;<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>6. Double down on Vitamin D.</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vitamin D is present in very few foods, so we get most of it from the sun. When we’re wearing sunscreen and full-coverage clothes, our skin has little opportunity to absorb this essential vitamin. As such, many doctors recommend taking Vitamin D supplements in the winter. In some <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/30820304\">studies</a>, Vitamin D has been shown to improve mood. (Always be sure to consult with your doctor before starting a vitamin regimen!)<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>7. Take a hydrating bath.</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A hot, bubbly bath may sound perfect in the winter, but we have some unfortunate news: hot baths can dehydrate the skin. Thankfully, there are ways to make your bathwater more moisturizing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Start with the temperature. A warm bath is far better for the skin than a scalding hot bath. Then, add hydrating ingredients like coconut oil or olive oil to make the water more nourishing. If your skin is feeling irritated, add colloidal oatmeal – not quite the same as your breakfast cereal – to the warm water. You can buy a pack at the store, or make your own by grinding whole, uncooked oats in a food processor until they form a light powder. Then, you\'re free to soak away.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the right mindset (and the right skincare), winter can be pretty charming. Light the candles, slather on the <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>, make yourself a cup of tea, and lean into cozy season. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Get Your Skin Ready for Winter','Are you ready for the chilly days of winter? Even if you love the cozy months, winter calls for a little more self care. Here are seven ways to take better care of your skin (and your soul) during winter.','publish','open','open','','how-to-get-your-skin-ready-for-winter','','','2019-12-11 16:24:40','2019-12-11 16:24:40','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=650',0,'post','',0),(635,3,'2019-11-22 13:14:56','2019-11-22 13:14:56','','product-images_5354_variants_2364_imgs_PDP_DEWSKIN_R29_05','','inherit','open','closed','','product-images_5354_variants_2364_imgs_pdp_dewskin_r29_05','','','2019-11-22 13:14:56','2019-11-22 13:14:56','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/product-images_5354_variants_2364_imgs_PDP_DEWSKIN_R29_05.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(636,3,'2019-11-22 13:19:44','2019-11-22 13:19:44','','Amika','','inherit','open','closed','','amika','','','2019-11-22 13:19:44','2019-11-22 13:19:44','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Amika.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(637,3,'2019-11-22 13:26:21','2019-11-22 13:26:21','','Bite-Beauty','','inherit','open','closed','','bite-beauty','','','2019-11-22 13:26:21','2019-11-22 13:26:21','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Bite-Beauty.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(638,3,'2019-11-22 13:37:42','2019-11-22 13:37:42','','Glowing-Gift-Set','','inherit','open','closed','','glowing-gift-set','','','2019-11-22 13:37:42','2019-11-22 13:37:42','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Glowing-Gift-Set.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(639,3,'2019-11-22 13:49:29','2019-11-22 13:49:29','','Burts-Bees','','inherit','open','closed','','burts-bees','','','2019-11-22 13:49:29','2019-11-22 13:49:29','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Burts-Bees.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(640,3,'2019-11-22 13:50:44','2019-11-22 13:50:44','','Amika The Kure','','inherit','open','closed','','amika-the-kure','','','2019-11-22 13:50:44','2019-11-22 13:50:44','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Amika-The-Kure.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(641,3,'2019-11-22 14:07:14','2019-11-22 14:07:14','','wet_lip_oil_gloss_dip_vessel_600x','','inherit','open','closed','','wet_lip_oil_gloss_dip_vessel_600x','','','2019-11-22 14:07:14','2019-11-22 14:07:14','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/wet_lip_oil_gloss_dip_vessel_600x.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(642,3,'2019-11-28 08:47:28','2019-11-28 08:47:28','','Mauna-Bronzer-Both-Alima-Pure','','inherit','open','closed','','mauna-bronzer-both-alima-pure','','','2019-11-28 08:47:28','2019-11-28 08:47:28','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Mauna-Bronzer-Both-Alima-Pure.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(646,3,'2019-11-28 09:36:29','2019-11-28 09:36:29','','Hello','','inherit','open','closed','','hello','','','2019-11-28 09:36:29','2019-11-28 09:36:29','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Hello.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(643,3,'2019-11-28 09:02:05','2019-11-28 09:02:05','','Alchemy-3-web','','inherit','open','closed','','alchemy-3-web','','','2019-11-28 09:02:05','2019-11-28 09:02:05','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Alchemy-3-web.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(644,3,'2019-11-28 09:04:01','2019-11-28 09:04:01','','Alchemy','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2019-11-28-at-10-05-09-am','','','2019-11-28 09:04:44','2019-11-28 09:04:44','',470,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screen-Shot-2019-11-28-at-10.05.09-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(655,3,'2019-12-11 16:25:53','2019-12-11 16:25:53','','The Gift of R+R (Replenish + Restore)','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-autosave-v1','','','2019-12-11 16:25:53','2019-12-11 16:25:53','',579,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/579-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(671,3,'2019-12-31 15:27:27','2019-12-31 15:27:27','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Is your skincare regimen ready for a new decade? We\'ve assembled a list of five new year\'s resolutions that promote healthy, radiant skin in 2020 (or any year, for that matter). The best part? They\'re so easy to follow you\'ll actually stick to them. </strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As <a href=\"https://dellmed.utexas.edu/directory/s-tyler-hollmig\">Dr. S. Tyler Hollmig</a>, the director of dermatologic surgery at the Dell Medical School at the University of Texas at Austin told us, \"It\'s the time of year where we are bombarded with \'new year, new you\' messaging from the beauty industry.\" (We\'re aware that the entire premise of this story makes us a little guilty, but just stick with us!)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We don\'t think you need a \"new you\" – we think you\'re wonderful as you are – but we do think the new year is a perfect time to set intentions and make sustainable changes for a healthier, happier life (and healthier, happier skin, too). Here\'s how to adjust your skincare regimen for more radiant skin in 2020. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">1. Don\'t forget to wash your face each night.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This may sound obvious, but Dr. Hollmig says neglecting this crucial step is more common than one might think. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Some of the best skincare advice for the new year often involves getting back to the basics.&nbsp;It always surprises me how many patients with acne-prone skin forget to cleanse and remove all of their makeup at the end of the day,\" Dr. Hollmig told us. \"This is a great resolution – use a gentle cleanser to remove all makeup, grime, and pollution every night to achieve healthier, more radiant skin.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">2. Marie Kondo your medicine cabinet. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>New year, new shelf space. You know all those products jamming up your medicine cabinet? It\'s time to get rid of what isn\'t working for you. If anything is expired, toss it in the recycling bin. If something is still good but never made it into your daily regimen, try donating to an organization that gives lightly used beauty and skincare products to women who will love them. A few to try are <a href=\"https://beautybus.org/product-donations/\">Beauty Bus</a>, <a href=\"https://www.family-to-family.org/share-your-beauty/\">Share Your Beauty</a>, and your local women\'s shelter. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">3. Get serious about the skin barrier. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'re a loyal reader of The Lab, you know that healthy skin requires a healthy skin barrier. Unfortunately, it\'s easy to harm our skin barrier when we\'re trying to help. How? Think over-exfoliation, long, hot showers, and upsetting your pH balance with too many skincare products. (<a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/the-press-is-buzzing-about-the-skin-barrier/\">Dive deep into the skin barrier here</a>.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, told&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.thezoereport.com/p/eighteen-bs-new-firm-replenish-serum-fills-a-gap-in-your-skincare-routine-you-probably-dont-know-exists-exclusive-18703335\">The Zoe Report</a>, “In our research, it became clear that one of the most disruptive things we do to our skin’s natural barrier is to cleanse and exfoliate. Cleansing is essential to healthy skin, of course, to remove dirt and make up. In the process, however, cleansers strip the barrier function of some important natural moisturizing factors.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s where b-silk™ protein comes in. Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/firm-replenish-serum\">Firm + Replenish Serum</a> was designed to replenish the natural skin barrier after cleaning and exfoliating. After sliding on some serum, use an Eighteen B moisturizer for a boost of hydration and added barrier protection. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://www.zeichnerdermatology.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Joshua Zeichner,</a> director of cosmetic and clinical research in dermatology at Mount Sinai Hospital in New York told <a href=\"https://www.whowhatwear.co.uk/how-to-treat-winter-skin-concerns\">Who What Wear</a> that a product to consider is our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a>. \"It contains a specially formulated silk protein that acts both as a barrier and a carrier – it forms a protective but breathable barrier over the skin and carries hydrating ingredients like ceramides to fill in cracks in the outer skin layer.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">4. Double down on the sunscreen.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wearing sunscreen daily is a popular new year\'s resolution (and rightfully so!) but Dr. Hollmig has one better: He recommends reapplying sunscreen midday. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"UVA light penetrates office window glass and can cause wrinkles, uneven skin tone, and even certain skin cancers, so even indoor workers benefit from a mid-day application of sun protection. Many of my patients have found using powder-based sunscreens is the way to go, since there is no need to remove one\'s makeup before use.&nbsp;Just keep an SPF powder in your purse and apply over your lunch break.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">5. Shop sustainably.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Keeping the environment in mind is always something we can always get behind. In 2020, we encourage making our beauty and skincare routines more sustainable. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here\'s a great place to start. Our proprietary ingredient, b-silk™&nbsp;protein is made through a sustainable <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/the-magic-of-fermentation-how-we-make-b-silk-protein/\">fermentation process</a> where the inputs are yeast, water, sugar, and salt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As our Chief Science Officer, Lindsay Wray, told&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://www.cosmeticsbusiness.com/news/article_page/Cosmetics_Business_forecasts_5_Global_Beauty_Trends_of_2020_in_new_report/160773\">Cosmetics Business</a></em>: “The ability to make naturally inspired materials using microbes overcomes many of the drawbacks of synthesised materials and materials extracted from nature.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Biotechnology processes are scalable, repeatable, and sustainable. For me, the most exciting aspect of biotechnology is that it offers the ability to make a vast variety of materials that we could not make any way else, for example spider silk. It is an incredibly versatile technology that can target so many functionalities that the beauty industry is looking for.” For more sustainable products we love, check out our gift guide <a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/eighteen-b-holiday-gift-guide-sustainable-products/\">here</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Happy 2020! Here\'s to a year of health, happiness, and glowing skin. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you\'d like us to cover? We\'d love to hear from you. Reach out at thelab@eighteenb.com. </em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','New Year\'s Resolutions for Radiant Skin in 2020','Is your skincare regimen ready for a new decade? We\'ve assembled a list of five new year\'s resolutions that promote healthy, radiant skin in 2020. They\'re so easy to follow you\'ll actually stick to them. ','publish','open','open','','new-year-resolutions-skin','','','2020-01-02 15:52:13','2020-01-02 15:52:13','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=671',0,'post','',0),(658,3,'2019-12-12 15:18:07','2019-12-12 15:18:07','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Is your holiday shopping underway? To help you prep for shopping season, we’ve assembled a gift guide series to highlight our favorite products, brands, and causes. Our third gift guide is dedicated to brands that value sustainability as much as we do.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some serious shopping goes down between Thanksgiving and Christmas, which leads to a lot of waste. According to a report by the <a href=\"https://www.neefusa.org/holiday-waste\">National Environmental Education Foundation</a>, Americans throw away 25% more trash from Thanksgiving to New Year\'s Day than any other time of year.&nbsp;To us, that means shopping responsibly is particularly important over the holidays.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sustainability is close to our hearts. Eighteen B began with b-silk™ protein, our innovative key ingredient. Our proprietary protein was inspired by the strong and lustrous properties of spider silk. Rather than harvesting silk from silkworms or spiders, however, our silk proteins are made through a fermentation process that uses simple and clean resources like sugar, water, yeast, and salt. That means our formulations are vegan, sustainable, and cruelty free.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here’s a guide to the products on our wish list made by brands with sustainability as a core value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong><a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/holidaysets/?utm_source=thelab&amp;utm_medium=thelab&amp;utm_campaign=lb_gg\">Shop Eighteen B holiday sets now (pretty and pre-packaged in a recyclable box).</a></strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">1. <strong>Sweater Sweatshirt by Pact</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":659,\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Sweater-Sweatshirt-Pact.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-659\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://wearpact.com/women/apparel/sweaters/sweater%20sweatshirt/wa1-wsw-jad\">Pact</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wish you could stay in your PJs all day? You\'re in luck. The <a href=\"https://wearpact.com/women/apparel/sweaters/sweater%20sweatshirt/wa1-wsw-jad\">Sweater Sweatshirt</a> by Pact has the casual, cozy feel of a sweatshirt with the polish of a sweater. The classic crew neck cut comes in Dark Navy and Jade. Pact uses 100% organic cotton, made without inorganic pesticides and fertilizers. That means there’s little to no water pollution in the process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">2. St Barths Large Tote by Naghedi</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":660,\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Naghedi.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-660\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.shopbop.com/barths-large-tote-naghedi/vp/v=1/1520982682.htm?folderID=47655&amp;fm=other-viewall&amp;os=false&amp;colorId=35835\">Shopbop</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sara Naghedi launched <a href=\"http://naghedinyc.com/about/\">Naghedi</a> as a casual alternative to her sustainable luxury brand, Deux Lux. These beautiful, woven bags are made from neoprene. This durable material can be used on land, in the sand, or by the sea. We particularly love the St Barths Large Tote, now available at <a href=\"https://www.shopbop.com/barths-large-tote-naghedi/vp/v=1/1520982682.htm?folderID=47655&amp;fm=other-viewall&amp;os=false&amp;colorId=35835\">Shopbop</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">3. Augusta Dress by Mara Hoffman</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":661,\"align\":\"center\",\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-661\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.marahoffman.com/swimwear/coverups/augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white\">Mara Hoffman</a></em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Is someone special heading to the tropics? <a href=\"https://www.marahoffman.com/\">Mara Hoffman</a> makes some of our favorite sustainable swimwear, and that includes her coverups. The <a href=\"https://www.marahoffman.com/swimwear/coverups/augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white\">Augusta Dress</a> is a breezy, semi-sheer coverup made with 100% organic cotton. With its elegant cut and fun v-neck in the back, this coverup will take her from the beach to sunset cocktails. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">4. V&amp;A Bamboo Print Obi Dress by People Tree</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":662,\"align\":\"center\",\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/va-bamboo-print-obi-dress-a14ea625cf06.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-662\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.peopletree.co.uk/new-in/va-bamboo-print-obi-dress\">People Tree</a></em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Adorable and eco-friendly, the <a href=\"https://www.peopletree.co.uk/new-in/va-bamboo-print-obi-dress\">V&amp;A Bamboo Print Obi Dress</a> by People Tree makes a festive addition to her wardrobe. The print was inspired by a traditional kimono in the V&amp;A Museum\'s Asian collection. The bamboo represents longevity, perseverance, and renewal – a perfect message to ring in the New Year. The material is 100%  Tencel™ Lyocell, made from cellulose fibers from wood pulp. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">5. Ribbed Robe by Kotn</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":666} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Kotn.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-666\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://us.kotn.com/collections/womens/products/ribbed-robe?variant=31239167049782\">Kotn</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\'Tis the season for lots of lounging. Make holing up at home even cozier with the <a href=\"https://us.kotn.com/collections/womens/products/ribbed-robe?variant=31239167049782\">Ribbed Robe</a> by Kotn. This warm, heavyweight robe is inspired by a classic kimono (just check out the voluminous sleeves). Kotn uses 100% Egyptian cotton that\'s ethically sourced, which means it\'s as soft as it is sustainable. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">6. Mellow Midnight Gift Set by Myro</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":664,\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PURPLE_crop_half_max-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-664\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.mymyro.com/pages/gifts\">Myro</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not so sure about deodorant as a gift? Myro has done the impossible: they\'ve made deodorant giftable. Myro makes \"deo pods\" that fit inside refillable containers so you use 50% less plastic when you refill. Their deodorants are vegan, cruelty-free, and aluminum-free. The <a href=\"https://www.mymyro.com/pages/gifts\">Mellow Midnight</a> set comes with a deo pod in Big Dipper, (bergamot, lavender, and vetiver), a reusable case, a lavender-scented eye mask, and a reusable gift bag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\">7. Breezy Britt jeans by Nudie Jeans Co. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://cdn.nudiejeans.com/img/Breezy_Britt_Black_Stone_113153_16_800x800.jpg\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption><em>Photo courtesy of <a href=\"https://www.nudiejeans.com/product/breezy-britt-black-stone\">Nudie Jeans</a></em></figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As denim lovers, we have our eye on the <a href=\"https://www.nudiejeans.com/product/breezy-britt-black-worn\">Breezy Britt</a> by Nudie Jeans. This Swedish brand uses raw denim made from organic cotton, intended to mold to your body as you wear them. It\'s not just the shape – the color of Nudie Jeans is meant to fade in all the right places. Consider these the perfect pair of vintage jeans you\'ve never found.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Eighteen B Holiday Gift Guide: Sustainable Products on our Wish List','At Eighteen B, sustainability is close to our hearts. For our third holiday gift guide, we\'re highlighting the sustainable brands on our shopping list. Here\'s our guide to the eco-friendly products we\'re loving.','publish','open','open','','eighteen-b-holiday-gift-guide-sustainable-products','','','2020-01-02 16:13:18','2020-01-02 16:13:18','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=658',0,'post','',0),(660,3,'2019-12-12 12:40:53','2019-12-12 12:40:53','','Naghedi','','inherit','open','closed','','naghedi','','','2019-12-12 12:40:53','2019-12-12 12:40:53','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Naghedi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(659,3,'2019-12-12 12:33:09','2019-12-12 12:33:09','','Sweater Sweatshirt Pact','','inherit','open','closed','','sweater-sweatshirt-pact','','','2019-12-12 12:33:09','2019-12-12 12:33:09','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Sweater-Sweatshirt-Pact.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(661,3,'2019-12-12 12:55:26','2019-12-12 12:55:26','','augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white_1','','inherit','open','closed','','augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white_1','','','2019-12-12 12:55:26','2019-12-12 12:55:26','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/augusta-v-back-ruffle-cover-up-dress-white_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(662,3,'2019-12-12 13:06:51','2019-12-12 13:06:51','','va-bamboo-print-obi-dress-a14ea625cf06','','inherit','open','closed','','va-bamboo-print-obi-dress-a14ea625cf06','','','2019-12-12 13:06:51','2019-12-12 13:06:51','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/va-bamboo-print-obi-dress-a14ea625cf06.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(663,3,'2019-12-12 13:24:41','2019-12-12 13:24:41','','MELLOW_MIDNIGHT-min','','inherit','open','closed','','mellow_midnight-min','','','2019-12-12 13:24:41','2019-12-12 13:24:41','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/MELLOW_MIDNIGHT-min.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(669,3,'2019-12-20 15:57:47','2019-12-20 15:57:47','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>We asked our community to help us find our next Eighteen B Woman, and you certainly delivered. We\'re thrilled to introduce you to Shannon Sherrell, entrepreneur, nonprofit founder, overall inspiration, and our newest Eighteen B Woman.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shannon Sherrell of Tallahassee, Florida runs a <a href=\"http://ssbeautytally.com/\">growing empire</a> of hair salons, spas, and beauty stores as well as a mentorship nonprofit. While these may sound like disparate ventures, to her they\'re intrinsically linked. Only she didn\'t know that when she got started. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shannon began styling hair professionally when she was a student at Florida State University. She saw clients in her home, mostly friends and family friends. Many of them, particularly the younger girls, opened up to Shannon, telling her about their problems with girls at school, relationships, and self confidence.&nbsp;She naturally became an ally, and eventually a mentor to these young girls. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These issues felt familiar to Shannon. “I had a very hard time in high school,\" she told us. \"I didn\'t have that confidante, that mentor that I would have liked to have.” During her last semester at Florida State University, she realized this idea could be turned into something bigger. “I realized that I had gone through what I went through so I could help others.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She founded LADIES in 2014 with the first chapter at her <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ladiesfsu/\">alma mater</a>. A second chapter at <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ladies_uf/\">University of Florida</a> was chartered shortly thereafter. An acronym for Leadership, Advancement, Development, Involvement, Encouragement, and Service, LADIES provides mentorship to high school girls.&nbsp;\"High school is a very important part of everybody’s lives, especially women. We go through a lot at that time: drama with other girls in school, boyfriends, first loves. These things mold who we are.”  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LADIES members tutor high schoolers in academic subjects, help them with college applications, and, perhaps most importantly, offer personal support. Mentors become these confidantes that Shannon wished she had had in high school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Shannon isn\'t bonding with the women in her chapters, she\'s expanding her <a href=\"https://ssbeautytally.com/\">beauty business</a>. Shannon is the owner of SSBeauty Bar, SSBeauty Spa, and SSBeauty Supply, all of which have opened since March 2018. “Beauty goes hand-in-hand with how I feel about mentorship. I\'m all about women’s empowerment and making women feel beautiful. It\'s about women supporting other women and not tearing them down.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shannon has high hopes for the futures of LADIES. There are two chapters in the works, and hopefully more to come. “We have a lot in store. We’re hoping to raise enough money to give ten mentees at least $1,000 for college scholarships.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I’m amazed at the growth that LADIES has had and I\'m very blessed to have the team to make LADIES even better than I had imagined.” To this day, Shannon still talks to the mentees she worked with in 2014. “It just goes to show that when you have that substance and you passionately and genuinely love what you’re doing, everything comes full circle.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shannon believes that all women can be mentors, even without organizations like LADIES. Her advice? \"Always be yourself and never feel like you\'re not enough, because the very thing that you have somebody else needs. The things you feel you lack are the things that make you beautiful and unique.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“When I was doing hair at my house when I was in college, I really bonded with those young ladies. So it doesn’t matter where you are – It doesn\'t matter where you are in life, and it doesn\'t matter where you are physically. What you have is more than enough to mentor and inspire somebody else.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>A big thanks to <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/KLadyPayne/\">Kara Payne</a> for introducing us to Shannon! Do you know our next Eighteen B Woman? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Eighteen B Woman: Shannon Sherrell','We asked our community to help us find our next Eighteen B Woman, and you certainly delivered. We\'re thrilled to introduce you to Shannon Sherrell, entrepreneur, nonprofit founder, and our newest Eighteen B Woman.','publish','open','open','','eighteen-b-woman-shannon-sherrell','','','2019-12-20 16:31:26','2019-12-20 16:31:26','',0,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=669',0,'post','',0),(664,3,'2019-12-12 13:40:59','2019-12-12 13:40:59','','PURPLE_crop_half_max-min (2)','','inherit','open','closed','','purple_crop_half_max-min-2','','','2019-12-12 13:40:59','2019-12-12 13:40:59','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PURPLE_crop_half_max-min-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(666,3,'2019-12-12 14:26:47','2019-12-12 14:26:47','','Kotn','','inherit','open','closed','','kotn','','','2019-12-12 14:26:47','2019-12-12 14:26:47','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Kotn.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(665,3,'2019-12-12 14:07:38','2019-12-12 14:07:38','','EighteenB Product','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb-product-5','','','2019-12-12 14:07:38','2019-12-12 14:07:38','',658,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/EighteenB-Product-x-The-House-That-Lars-Built-4830.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(670,3,'2019-12-20 15:34:26','2019-12-20 15:34:26','','Shannon Sherrell','','inherit','open','closed','','shannon-sherrell','','','2019-12-20 15:34:26','2019-12-20 15:34:26','',669,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Shannon-Sherrell.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(675,3,'2020-01-13 12:03:27','2020-01-13 12:03:27','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>B</strong></em><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\">-silk™ protein,</strong> <em><strong>our proprietary polypeptide,</strong></em><b><em><strong> finally has an official INCI name. Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, </strong></em></b><em><strong>gives us</strong></em><strong><em> the low-down on what an INCI name means, how we got ours, and why it matters.</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Exciting news: B-silk™ protein has officially received an INCI name! Meet sr-Wasp Spider Polypeptide-1 Oligopeptide-178.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not as excited as I am? Stay with me. Learning how to read an INCI name is essential to understanding what’s in your products. Read on to learn why.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>What does INCI stand for ?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>INCI (pronounced “inky”) stands for the International Nomenclature of Cosmetic Ingredients. INCI names are chosen by the International Nomenclature Committee (INC) and published by the Personal Care Products Council (PCPC). INCI names are a systematic way to label chemicals specifically for the cosmetic industry. You might be asking, “Don’t chemicals already have names? Why do they need another?” That’s a good question. There\'s also a good answer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Why do INCI names exist?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>INCI names ensure there is only one name for each ingredient worldwide. According to Rachel Quirk, our Associate Director of Quality &amp; Regulatory (who had a hand in this process from start to finish), “All countries accept and most <em>expect</em> ingredients to be listed using their INCI name. Why? If an ingredient goes by multiple names, it can be hard to keep track of all the scientific information associated with an ingredient. It also becomes hard to track the regulatory and safety status of an ingredient.”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>INCI names make it easy for consumers, the cosmetic industry, and the medical community to identify ingredients, no matter where they come from. This is particularly important for consumers with allergies, or those who avoid certain ingredients for ethical reasons. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How did b-silk™ protein get an INCI name? “INCI asks for <a href=\"http://www.personalcarecouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/INCI-Application-Complete-Details.pdf\">a LOT of information</a> in the application,\" Rachel told us. \"We had to provide the chemical structure, compositional information, and a detailed step-by-step of the manufacturing method. For peptides, they ask for <a href=\"https://pcpcouncilstg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/AddendumPeptides.pdf\">additional information</a>, including the full peptide sequence.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>So, what does sr-Wasp Spider Polypeptide-1 Oligopeptide-178 mean?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How did we get the name <strong>sr-Wasp Spider Polypeptide-1 Oligopeptide-178</strong>? Let’s break it down.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>“Sr-”</strong> stands for “synthetic recombinant.” “Recombinant” means our silk was made by <em>recombining</em> the silk DNA sequence you find in spiders with the DNA of our fermentation organism (in our case, a yeast). “Synthetic” means we did not use a perfect copy of the natural DNA; we shortened it a bit for optimal performance.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>“Wasp Spider”</strong> is the common name for <em>Argiope bruennichi</em>, the spider species that makes b-silk™ protein in nature. Why did we choose this spider silk to model our b-silk™ protein after? The wasp spider evolved to make a very special silk, one that hits the sweet spot for being strong but also elastic, effectively combining the powers of collagen and elastin into one.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A quick digression: We were excited to get the “wasp spider” designation. After all, you couldn’t ask for a more badass set of bugs as a namesake! However, we were a little surprised that a very important word is missing from the name: <em>silk</em>. Spiders make a lot of different proteins (like venom, for example). How is a consumer to know that our ingredient comes from spider silk and not another spider protein? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Secondly, there doesn’t seem to be much consistency behind how animal names are assigned to proteins. Sometimes INC uses the common name (as in our case), but other times they use the latin name. Even then, the latin name can come from different levels within the taxonomic ranking. As the role of an INCI name is to provide transparency for the consumer, these two points may add confusion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>“Polypeptide-1” </strong>means that our protein has more than 100 amino acids, which makes b-silk™ protein a high molecular weight protein. This is what sets b-silk™ protein apart from hydrolyzed silk, which is commonly found in cosmetics. We are “-1” because we are the first polypeptide inspired by wasp spider to apply for an INCI name.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally,<strong> “Oligopeptide-178”</strong> indicates that we have a small sequence on the end of our protein that was not derived from spider. This is less than 100 amino acids long. We are the 178th oligopeptide to get an INCI name.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We’re proud to have an INCI name because it shows our commitment to transparency and our dedication to innovation. And that drive to innovate is what makes us at Eighteen B who we are. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Want to learn more about how we created b-silk™  protein? We thought you\'d never ask. </strong></em><a href=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/the-magic-of-fermentation-how-we-make-b-silk-protein/\"><em><strong>Click here for the full story</strong></em></a><em><strong>.</strong></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions for Lindsay? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ask Lindsay: We Got Our INCI Name! Here’s why it matters.','B-silk™ protein, our proprietary polypeptide, finally has an official INCI name. Lindsay Wray, our Chief Science Officer, gives us the low-down on what an INCI name means, how we got ours, and why it matters.','publish','open','open','','what-is-an-inci-name','','','2020-01-13 14:27:31','2020-01-13 14:27:31','',0,'http://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=675',0,'post','',0),(676,3,'2020-01-13 11:57:55','2020-01-13 11:57:55','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1370','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1370-3','','','2020-01-13 11:57:55','2020-01-13 11:57:55','',675,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1370.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(677,3,'2020-01-20 06:00:52','2020-01-20 06:00:52','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>The thin, delicate skin around the eyes needs a little extra love. Here\'s why you need and eye cream, and why Eighteen B\'s new Defend + Nourish Eye Cream covers all your bases</em></strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You <em>might</em> have noticed: the skin around your eyes seems to age faster than the rest of your face. Your eyes aren’t deceiving you – this skin often is the first to wrinkle thanks (but no thanks) to a few unique circumstances. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h2 style=\"text-align:left\">Here\'s why.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">1. The skin around your eyes is THIN.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The skin around the eyes, also known as periorbital skin, is the thinnest skin on your face. And we mean <em>thin</em> – up to ten times thinner than the rest of your face. That means it lacks the cushy collagen and elastin that keep skin looking plump and healthy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We hate to be the bearer of bad news, but this skin keeps thinning. As we grow wiser, our skin starts to <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6047276/\">produce less collagen and elastin</a>. These fibers that connect to the epidermis get weaker, which means our skin begins to show wrinkles. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">2. This skin is not very good at moisturizing itself.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our skin naturally creates oils and lipids to keep itself moisturized and protected. However, the skin around the eye has far fewer sebaceous glands, which means it produces less natural moisturizer on its own. These lipids are very important to the skin barrier function, which provides essential protection from the elements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As we age, our sweat and oil glands also become less active, which makes the skin even drier. Of course, fine lines and wrinkles look more obvious on dry and dehydrated skin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:left\">3. Your eyes are always on the move.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Think about it – you spend all day smiling, squinting, blinking, winking back at hotties on the subway. <a href=\"https://www.npr.org/2011/02/25/134059275/looking-at-what-the-eyes-see\">Scientists estimate</a> that we move our eyes approximately three times per second, which adds up to 100,000 times each day. That\'s a lot of action for such delicate skin! You need to do all you can to protect it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h2 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Okay, the skin needs some serious protection. But why do I need an eye cream AND a moisturizer?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A fair question! Here\'s the answer: You want an eye cream to be rich enough to deliver the moisture you need, but you don\'t want it to be overpowering. The skin around the eyes is delicate. It\'s easily irritated and your eyeballs themselves are very sensitive. (Our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/hydrate-restore-rich-cream/\">Hydrate + Restore Rich Cream</a> and our <a href=\"https://www.eighteenb.com/silk-facial-moisturizers/defend-nourish-eye-cream/\">Defend + Nourish Eye Cream</a> are both opthamologist-tested, meaning they\'re safe to wear close to the lashline. ) For some people, an overly nourishing cream can cause milia (little bumps under the eye). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That means an eye cream needs to strike a delicate balance. It needs to be potent with a high density of active ingredients, but it also needs to be lightweight and gentle. As many people top their eye cream with concealer or foundation, it also needs to layer well with makeup. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h2 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>Got it: I need an eye cream. Why does Eighteen B’s Defend + Nourish Eye Cream</strong> fit the bill?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eighteen B goes where other eye creams haven\'t gone before: we defend the delicate skin around the eye by supporting the skin barrier. Defend + Nourish Eye Cream is packed with B-silk™ Protein, our one-of-a-kind polypeptide that delivers powerful ingredients to this delicate skin while skillfully defending your natural skin barrier. B-silk™ Protein forms a lightweight, protective barrier that keeps active ingredients close to the skin so they can do their work. The result? Smoother, more rested looking eyes with less visible wrinkles and faded dark circles. <strong>In other words, it’s the eye cream that breaks barriers by building yours.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for those active ingredients, B-silk™ Protein carries some seriously powerful ingredients to the skin. Hydration comes courtesy of potent emollients and humectants like Squalane, Jojoba Oil, and Hyaluronic Acid. Jasmine Flower Extract helps improve circulation to banish the appearance of dark circles. Finally, Watermelon Rind Extract, Lentil Fruit Extract, and Apple Extract hydrate and replenish skin to reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and crepiness. You won’t believe your eye cream.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h2 style=\"text-align:left\">PS: <strong>You’re going to love the texture.&nbsp;</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The rich texture quickly absorbs but leaves a presence, meaning it lays a great foundation for concealer (if you even need it).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":685} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/EighteenB_11-21-19_037_web.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-685\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Felicia Walker, the skincare and beauty expert behind the award-winning blog <a href=\"http://thisthatbeauty.com/\">ThisThatBeauty</a>, gave us her hot take on Defend + Nourish Eye Cream. “Defend + Nourish Eye Cream plays very well with concealer, which is not true of a lot of eye creams. Some of them need time to set. Some of them pill or roll off once you put the makeup on. It plays well in the sandbox with your cosmetics.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The texture feels very cloud-like, with a plump, cushiony feel. It absorbs fast, but it leaves a presence. That’s what I want in an eye cream. I don’t want to be glistening like a disco ball, but I do want a bit of reflective quality.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Felicia let us in on one of her favorite eye cream tips: “One little hack that I like to do is create a BB cream with my concealer. I\'ll mix a little bit of the eye cream and concealer together to give the makeup a bit more bounce. Then the concealer moves with your skin, versus settling into those creases and fine lines.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We were able to achieve that texture the clean way. Defend + Nourish Eye Cream is opthamologist-tested, EWG Verified, Leaping Bunny Certified, Vegan, and formulated without Silicones, Parabens, Mineral Oil, or Petrolatum.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h2 style=\"text-align:left\">And it really works.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How do we know? Because we put it to the test.&nbsp;In a consumer trial across 100 women over 28 days, participants saw smoother wrinkles, reduced crow\'s feet, and a more nourished appearance in just 7 days. Over time, results got even better. How is this possible? Our proprietary B-silk™ Protein. It’s that good. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Do you have questions? Comments? Topics you want us to cover? We’d love to hear from you. Email us at thelab@eighteenb.com.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Here\'s Why You Need an Eye Cream','The thin, delicate skin around the eyes needs a little extra love. Here\'s why you need an eye cream, and how Eighteen B\'s new Defend + Nourish Eye Cream covers all your bases.','publish','open','open','','why-you-need-eye-cream','','','2020-01-21 12:49:11','2020-01-21 12:49:11','',0,'http://blog.eighteenb.com/?p=677',0,'post','',0),(678,3,'2020-01-15 15:40:26','2020-01-15 15:40:26','','20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1311','','inherit','open','closed','','20190622_dbaum_eighteenb_editorial_1311-2','','','2020-01-15 15:40:26','2020-01-15 15:40:26','',677,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20190622_DBaum_EighteenB_Editorial_1311.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(681,3,'2020-01-15 18:21:37','2020-01-15 18:21:37','','B-SILK™ PROTEIN Defend + Nourish Eye Cream','','publish','closed','closed','','b-silk-protein-defend-nourish-eye-cream','','','2020-01-15 18:21:37','2020-01-15 18:21:37','',0,'http://blog.eighteenb.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=681',0,'product','',0),(682,3,'2020-01-15 18:18:40','2020-01-15 18:18:40','','Defend + Nourish Eye Cream Front Facing Cap Off','','inherit','open','closed','','defend-nourish-eye-cream-front-facing-cap-off','','','2020-01-15 18:18:40','2020-01-15 18:18:40','',681,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Defend-Nourish-Eye-Cream-Front-Facing-Cap-Off.tif',0,'attachment','image/tiff',0),(683,3,'2020-01-15 18:20:49','2020-01-15 18:20:49','','Screen Shot 2020-01-15 at 7.22.22 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2020-01-15-at-7-22-22-pm','','','2020-01-15 18:20:49','2020-01-15 18:20:49','',681,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Screen-Shot-2020-01-15-at-7.22.22-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(685,3,'2020-01-20 18:24:18','2020-01-20 18:24:18','','EighteenB_11-21-19_037_web','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteenb_11-21-19_037_web','','','2020-01-20 18:24:18','2020-01-20 18:24:18','',677,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/EighteenB_11-21-19_037_web.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(687,3,'2020-01-21 12:55:40','2020-01-21 12:55:40','','eighteen B 10-15-193623_web','','inherit','open','closed','','eighteen-b-10-15-193623_web','','','2020-01-21 12:55:40','2020-01-21 12:55:40','',552,'https://blog.eighteenb.com/wp-content/up